Zabrus chiosanus is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is endemic to the North Aegean islands .
Cyathea biformis is a species of tree fern native to New Guinea and the Maluku Islands , where it grows against trees in mossy forest and rain forest at an altitude of 850 - -2200 m. The climbing trunk is very thin , only 1 - -2 cm in diameter , but can reach 3 m in height .
Mesosetum is a genus of Neotropical plants in the grass family , native to North and South America including the West Indies .
Baoule 's mouse ( Mus baoulei ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

Copidoris dimorpha is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Copidoris .
Dendriscocaulon is a taxonomic name that has been used for a genus of fruticose lichen ( shrubby form lichen ) with a cyanobacteria as the photobiont partner of the fungus .
Cipactlichthys is a genus of extinct Holostean fish from the Lower Cretaceous of Mexico .

Awaous grammepomus , the Scribbled goby , is a species of goby native to freshwater streams and rivers and brackish estuaries from Sri Lanka to New Guinea with a report of it occurring in Palau .
Muellerolimon salicorniaceum , the sole species in genus Muellerolimon , is a succulent perennial herb or shrub that grows on salt mudflats in Western Australia .

Cotoneaster kansuensis is a species of flowering plant in the Rosaceae family that can be found in Gansu province of Central China .
Heteroclinus heptaeolus , Ogilby 's weedfish , is a species of clinid native to the coast of southern Australia where it can be found in habitats with plentiful seaweed growth .

Tropidophorus is a genus of semiaquatic lizards in the skink family ( Scincidae ) , found in Indochina , Borneo , Sulawesi , and the Philippines .
Koordersiochloa is a widespread genus of plants in the grass family , native to Africa , tropical Asia , and various islands in the Indian Ocean .
Orbicella annularis , commonly known as the boulder star coral , is a species of coral that lives in the western Atlantic Ocean and is the most thoroughly studied and most abundant species of reef - building coral in the Caribbean to date .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Septopezizella oreadum .

Sanicula maritima is a rare species of flowering plant in the parsley family known by the common names adobe snakeroot and adobe sanicle .
Jassa marmorata is a species of tube - building amphipod .
Gaultheria procumbens , also called the eastern teaberry , the checkerberry , the boxberry , or the American wintergreen , is a species of Gaultheria native to northeastern North America from Newfoundland west to southeastern Manitoba , and south to Alabama .

Cirsonella globosa is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae , the turban snails .
The Sri Lanka petite shrub frog , Pseudophilautus tanu , is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to Sri Lanka .

Drosera meristocaulis is a perennial species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera , the only member of the subgenus Meristocaulis .
Harpaphe haydeniana ( the yellow - spotted millipede , almond - scented millipede or cyanide millipede ) is a species of polydesmidan ( `` flat - backed '' ) millipede found in the moist forests along the Pacific coast of North America , from Southeast Alaska to California .

Cerosterna is a genus of flat - faced longhorns beetle belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Lamiinae . The members are found in the Indomalaya ecozone .
Chiasognathus grantii is a species of stag beetle found in Argentina and Chile .
Eldeceeon is an extinct genus of reptiliomorph from the Early Carboniferous of Scotland .
Trachodon ( meaning `` rough tooth '' ) is a dubious genus of hadrosaurid dinosaur based on teeth from the Campanian - age Upper Cretaceous Judith River Formation of Montana , U.S. It is a historically important genus with a convoluted taxonomy that has been all but abandoned by modern dinosaur paleontologists .
Arenivaga floridensis is a species of sand cockroaches of the subfamily Polyphaginae , in the family Polyphagidae .
Duabanga is a small genus of lowland evergreen rainforest trees in southeast Asia , comprising two or three species .
Heterometrus kanarensis is a scorpion species found in Karnataka state of India .
Ceratosoma amoenum , or the clown nudibranch , is a species of colorful dorid nudibranch , a sea slug , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chromodorididae .
Phelsuma lineata , the lined day gecko , is a species of diurnal gecko native to Madagascar .
The tribe Anthocharini is one of the subdivisions of the insect order Lepidoptera , which includes the moths and butterflies .
Trypanosoma cruzi is a species of parasitic euglenoid protozoan .
Thermotoga is a genus of the phylum Thermotogae .
Paratritania alternans is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paratritania .

Sharfia mirabilis is an extinct species of anglerfish in the family Lophiidae .
Selaginella bigelovii is a species of spikemoss known by the common names bushy spikemoss and Bigelow 's spikemoss .
Amauriopsis dissecta is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common names yellow ragweed and ragleaf bahia .
Amphipogon , greybeard grasses , is a genus of Australian plants in the grass family .
Shorea almon ( also called Light Red Meranti , Philippine Mahogany , or White Lauan ) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Anthosachne sacandros is a species of true grass in the Triticeae tribe .
Strophomenida is a large , extinct order of articulate brachiopods that existed from the lower Ordovician to the lower Jurassic period .
Scapteriscus abbreviatus , the short - winged mole cricket , is a species of insect in the mole cricket family , Gryllotalpidae .
Preuss 's red colobus ( Procolobus preussi ) is a red colobus primate species endemic to the Cross - Sanaga Rivers ecoregion .
Diaethria ceryx or Ceryx Eighty - eight is a species of butterfly of the Diaethria genus .
Odorrana leporipes is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is endemic to Guangdong province of China .
Antennaria solitaria is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name singlehead pussytoes .
Fritillaria micrantha , known by the common names brown fritillary and brown bells , is a California species of fritillary in the lily family .
Oniscus asellus , the common woodlouse , is one of the largest and most common species of woodlouse in the British Isles and Western and Northern Europe , growing to lengths of 16 mm and widths of 6 mm .
Hassar affinis is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Parnaiba River basin .
Nebria wallowae is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to the US state of Oregon .
It contains the single species Phylolestes ethelae , the Hispaniolan malachite .
Allium chienchuanense is a plant species endemic to the Province of Yunnan in southern China .
The Melanorosauridae were a family of sauropodomorph dinosaurs which lived during the Late Triassic and Early Jurassic .
Carcharhinus tjutjot , also known as the Indonesian whaler shark is a species of requiem shark , belonging to the family Carcharhinidae .
Stokesiidae is a ciliate protozoa family in the order peniculida .
Mondegodon is an extinct genus of basal `` mesonychian '' which existed in Portugal , during the earliest Eocene ( Neustrian age ) .
Bradyrhizobium elkanii is a species of legume - root nodulating , microsymbiotic nitrogen - fixing bacterium originally identified as DNA homology group II strains of B. japonicum .
Nesolestes pauliani is a species of damselfly in the family Megapodagrionidae .
The red - sided curly - tailed lizard ( Leiocephalus schreibersii ) , also known as the Hispaniolan curlytail lizard , is a common lizard species native to the Caribbean , though an established introduced population can be found in southern Florida .
Eridantes is a genus of Money spider .
Olgaspis is an extinct genus of trilobite arthropods .
Agathidium is a genus of beetles in the family Leiodidae .
The type species is Mawsonites spriggi , named after Douglas Mawson , and Reg Sprigg .
Timimus is a genus of small coelurosaurian theropod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous of Australia .
Platythelphusa is a genus of freshwater crabs endemic to Lake Tanganyika .
Gomphus quadricolor , the rapids clubtail , is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Simochromis pleurospilus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is known to occur in rock rubble areas in the southwestern portion of the lake .
Ceanothus parryi , with the common name Parry ceanothus , is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae .
Retortamonas intestinalis is a species of retortamonad which is found in the gastrointestinal tract .
The Amur catfish , or Japanese common catfish , Silurus asotus , is a species of catfish ( sheatfish ) , family Siluridae .
Arrhenatherum elatius , with the common names false oat - grass , tall oat - grass , tall meadow oat , onion couch and tuber oat - grass , is a perennial species of grass , common in the temperate regions of Europe .
Neivamyrmex is a genus of army ants in the subfamily Dorylinae .
Orthetrum testaceum is an Asian freshwater dragonfly species .
Myriopteron is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1844 .
Ostrea equestris , or the crested oyster , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Ostreidae .
Fistulobalanus is a genus of barnacles , comprising the following species :
Juncus bolanderi is a species of rush known by the common name Bolander 's rush .
Boninofatsia is a genus of shrubs of family Araliaceae , with two species .
Mnesithea ( called Jointtail Grass ) is a genus of Asian , Australian , and Pacific Island plants in the grass family .
Gagea granatellii is a Mediterranean and Black Sea species of plants in the lily family .
Eupoecila inscripta , is a species of scarab beetle in the genus Eupoecila , found in western Australia .
Arctostaphylos pechoensis is a species of manzanita known by the common name Pecho manzanita .
Aguascalientia panamaensis is an extinct species of miniature camels found in Panama first described by Aldo F. Rincon et al .
Conus lizardensis , common name the Siboga cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Bromus briziformis is a species of brome grass known by the common name rattlesnake brome .
Rice grassy stunt virus ( RGSV ) is a plant pathogenic virus transmitted by the brown planthopper , Nilaparvata lugens , and two other Nilaparvata species , N. bakeri and N. muiri .
Phymatolithon is a genus of nongeniculate coralline red alga , known from the UK .
Pteria penguin , commonly known as the penguin 's wing oyster , is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Pteriidae , the pearl oysters .
Scaevola coriacea , the dwarf naupaka , is a species of flowering plant in the Goodenia family , Goodeniaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Trichalcidion penicillum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Trichalcidion .
Spiranthes infernalis , common name Ash Meadows lady 's tresses , is a rare species of orchid known from only four locations in Nevada , all close to one another .
Idolopsalis is a genus of earwigs , the sole member of the subfamily Idolopsalinae .
Bonagota salubricola , the Brazilian apple leafroller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Aquilegia pyrenaica , common name Pyrenean columbine , is a species of flowering plant in the family Ranunculaceae .
Capsicum baccatum is a species of chili pepper that includes the following cultivars :
Aptenia is a small genus of flowering plants in the family Aizoaceae .
Bithynia siamensis is a species of a freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic prosobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Bithyniidae .
Castilleja , commonly known as Indian paintbrush or prairie - fire , is a genus of about 200 species of annual and perennial herbaceous plants native to the west of the Americas from Alaska south to the Andes , northern Asia , and one species as far west as the Kola Peninsula in northwestern Russia .
Diadema antillarum , also known as the lime urchin , black sea urchin , Grabaskey 's bane or the long - spined sea urchin , is a species of sea urchin in the Family Diadematidae .
Castilleja parviflora is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name mountain Indian paintbrush .
Todea papuana , the Papuan King Fern is a species of fern known only from Papua - New Guinea .
Pinthaeus sanguinipes is a species of stink bug ( family Pentatomidae ) .
Xenomyrmex is a genus of small ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Tarsistes philippii is a taxonomically dubious species of guitarfish , family Rhinobatidae .
Iris stolonifera is a species in the genus Iris ; it is also in the subgenus of Iris , and in the Regelia section .
Glyceria striata is a species of mannagrass known by the common names fowl mannagrass and ridged glyceria .
Quercus cerrioides is an oak species of plant in the Fagaceae family .
Acernaspis is an extinct genus of Trilobite that is known from the Silurian .
Psenocerus supernotatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Psenocerus .
Mycale grandis , the orange keyhole sponge , is a species of marine demosponge in the family Mycalidae .
Cramauchenia is an extinct genus member of the litoptern order of South American mammals .
Alophonotus rauana is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Alophonotus .
Camacinia othello is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae known commonly as the black knight .
Hebeloma gigaspermum is a European species of mushroom in the Hymenogastraceae family .
Viverroidea is an infraorder of feliformia , containing both the family viverridae , and the superfamily herpestoidea .
Torreya clarnensis is an extinct species of conifer in the yew family Taxaceae solely known from the middle Eocene sediments exposed in north central Oregon .
Pseudonicarete peyrierasi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudonicarete .
Nastanthus falklandicus ( also called False - plantain ) is a species of plant in the Calyceraceae family .
Vitis betulifolia is a widely ranging species of liana in the grape family native to China ( found in Gansu , Henan , Hubei , Hunan , Shaanxi , Sichuan and Yunnan provinces ) where its habitat is forested or shrubby valleys and hillsides , at elevations from 600 to 3,600 metres ( 2,000 to 11,800 ft ) .
Diamphidia nigroornata or Bushman arrow - poison beetle , is an African leaf beetle species in the genus Diamphidia .
Aenigmastacus crandalli is a species of fossil freshwater crayfish .
Xantho hydrophilus ( also known as Xantho incisus and various other scientific names ) is a species of crab .
Forcipiger longirostris , commonly known as the longnose butterflyfish or big longnose butterflyfish , is a species of butterflyfish found on coral reefs throughout the tropical waters of the Indo - Pacific .
The Sunda minivet ( Pericrocotus miniatus ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
The Herpelidae are the family of common caecilians .
Eremiaphila luxor , common name Luxor mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Egypt .
Idanophana gephyra is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Idanophana of the family Ulidiidae .
Azaera nodoses is a species of snout moth in the genus Azaera .
Nonia exiguella is a species of snout moth , and the type species in the genus Nonia .
Cryptacanthodes is a genus of perciform fishes commonly referred to as wrymouths .
According to the previous taxonomy of the Gastropoda ( Ponder & Lindberg , 1997 ) Systellommatophora was considered to be a suborder or an order .
The Sepsidae are a family of flies , commonly called the black scavenger flies or ensign flies .
Aglyptodactylus securifer is a species of frog in the family Mantellidae .
Ceriagrion mourae is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae endemic to eastern Sub - Saharan Africa , most commonly in Mozambique and Tanzania .
Pollimyrus is a genus of elephantfishes native to Africa .
Treubia is a genus of liverworts in the family Treubiaceae .
The family Fagaceae includes beeches and oaks , and comprises about 600 species of both evergreen and deciduous trees and shrubs , which are characterized by alternate simple leaves with pinnate venation , unisexual flowers in the form of catkins , and fruit in the form of cup - like ( cupule ) nuts .
Hyla zhaopingensis is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to China .
Prorivulus auriferus is a species of rivuline endemic to northeastern Brazil where it is found in the coastal plains .
Salix babylonica ( Babylon willow or weeping willow ; Chinese : 垂柳 ) is a species of willow native to dry areas of northern China , but cultivated for millennia elsewhere in Asia , being traded along the Silk Road to southwest Asia and Europe .
Thelypteris aculeata is a species of fern in the Thelypteridaceae family .
Heteristius cinctus , the banded stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Pacific coast of the Americas from Baja California , Mexico to Ecuador where it can be found on sandy bottoms at depths of from 1 to 27 m ( 3.3 to 88.6 ft ) .
Calliostoma pulchrum , common name the beautiful top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Dasylirion longissimum , the Mexican Grass Tree , is a species of flowering plant native to the Chihuahuan Desert and other xeric habitats in Northeastern Mexico .
Bryaninops natans , known commonly as the Redeye goby , is a species of marine fish in the family Gobiidae .
It contains only one species , Kallimoides rumia , the African Leaf Butterfly .
Bathypolypus valdiviae , common name the boxer octopus , is a species of octopus in the Octopodidae family .
Streptomyces carpinensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Carpina in Pernambuco in Brazil .
Grapholita pallifrontana is a moth species of the family Tortricidae , subfamily Olethreutinae .
Marshallia mohrii , Mohr 's Barbara 's buttons , is a perennial herb species , endemic to the Southeastern United States , in several locations in Alabama , Georgia , and Florida .
Megalobatrachonema is a nematode genus .
Deer ( singular and plural ) are the ruminant mammals forming the family Cervidae .
Anthonomus is a genus of weevils .
Harposporium is a genus of anamorphic fungi within the Ophiocordycipitaceae family .
Petropedetes natator , also called the saber - toothed frog , is a species of frog in the Petropedetidae family found in Ivory Coast , Guinea , Liberia , and Sierra Leone .
Omobranchus anolius , the oyster blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Aerodramus is a genus of small , dark , cave - nesting birds in the Collocaliini tribe of the swift family .
Rosieria is a genus of dwarf cynodont from the Late Triassic of France .
Cryptantha scoparia is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Miners candle .
It contains only one species , Compsocrita florens , which is found in Brazil .
The Maui island - aster or Maui hesperomannia ( Hesperomannia arbuscula ) is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family that is endemic to the islands of Oʻahu and Maui in Hawaiʻi .
Raninidae is a family of unusual crabs , sometimes known as `` frog crabs '' , on account of their frog - like appearance .
Mobula eregoodootenkee ( the pygmy devil ray or longhorned mobula ) is a species of eagle ray in the genus Mobula .
The genus Attheya consist of small single celled diatoms .
Patiriella brevispina , also known as purple seastar is an Australian species of sea star .
Thaumatogryllus conanti is a nocturnal species of cricket endemic to the island of Nihoa , where it is found in Devil 's Slide , a narrow ravine .
Ticholeptus is an extinct genus of oreodont endemic to North America during the Early Miocene - Middle Miocene epochs ( 20.6 - -13.6 mya ) , existing for approximately 7 million years .
Margarites costalis , common name the boreal rosy margarite or the northern ridged margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
The Garo spineless eel , Garo khajuriai , is a species of earthworm eel endemic to India .
Neocrepidodera brevicollis is a species of flea beetle from a leaf beetle family that can be found in Austria , Czech Republic , Denmark , France , Germany , Italy , Poland , Slovakia , Sweden , and Switzerland .
Amboroa is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae described as a genus in 1956 .
Laevaricella is a genus of tropical , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Oleacinidae .
Fraser 's rufous thrush ( Neocossyphus fraseri ) , also known as the rufous flycatcher - thrush , is a species of bird in the thrush family .
Chlorophytum inornatum is a flowering plant species in the genus Chlorophytum .
Cretoxyrhinidae is an extinct family of sharks .
Trypaea australiensis , known as the ( marine ) yabby or ghost nippers in Australia and as the Australian ghost shrimp elsewhere , is a common species of mud shrimp in south - eastern Australia , the only species in the genus Trypaea .
Tonicella undocaerulea , commonly known as the Blue Lined Chiton , is a species of chiton .
The Braconidae is a large family of parasitoid wasps .
The genus consists of a single species , Concoctio concenta , known from tropical Africa .
Bullichthys is an extinct genus of albuliform fish which existed in Brazil during the Lower Cretaceous period .
Acer palmatum , called Japanese maple or smooth Japanese - maple ( Japanese : irohamomiji , イロハモミジ , or momiji , 紅葉 ) is a species of woody plant native to Japan , North Korea , South Korea , eastern Mongolia , and southeast Russia .
Torquigener vicinus is a species of fish in the family Tetraodontidae .
Paranemachilus is a genus of stone loaches endemic to China .
It contains the single species Darantasiella javanica , which is found on Java .
Quetecsaurus is an extinct genus of titanosaur sauropod dinosaur known from the Late Cretaceous of southern Mendoza Province of western Argentina .
Isolepis carinata ( syn . Scirpus koilolepis ) is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name keeled bulrush .
Labicymbium otti is a species of sheet weaver found in Brazil .
It has only one species , Sandersonia aurantiaca .
Perissodus is a genus of cichlids endemic to Lake Tanganyika .
Urticicola perchtae is a fossil species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , from the Early / Middle Miocene of Sandelzhausen ( type locality ) and Oggenhausen , southern Germany .
Cancer productus , one of several species known as red rock crabs , is a crab of the genus Cancer found on the western coast of North America .
Mitilanotherium is an extinct genus of giraffe from the Pliocene and Pleistocene of Europe .
Protoceratidae is an extinct family of herbivorous North American artiodactyls ( even - toed ungulates ) that lived during the Eocene through Pliocene at around 46.2 - -4.9 Mya , existing for about 41 million years .
Dunn 's mud turtle ( Kinosternon dunni ) , also known as the Colombian mud turtle , is a species of turtle in the Kinosternidae family .
Aipysurus laevis is a species of venomous sea snake found in the Indo - Pacific .
Anchomenidius feldmanni is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that is endemic to Spain .
Typhlops cariei commonly known as Hoffstetter 's worm snake is an extinct blind snake species which was endemic to Mauritius .
Tetrarhynchia is an extinct genus of brachiopod found in Jurassic strata in Europe and South America .
Isocoma rusbyi , the Rusby 's goldenbush , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Opuntia macrorhiza is a common and widespread species of cactus with the common names plains prickly pear or twistspine pricklypear or Western pricklypear .
Geohintonia mexicana ( discovered in 1992 ) is a species of cacti , the only species in the genus Geohintonia .
Cryptotrema is a genus of labrisomid blennies native to the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Mionothropus is an extinct genus of nothrotheriine nothrotheriid sloth which existed in Peru in western Amazonia , during the late Miocene ( Huayquerian age ) .
Chaetopterus or the parchment worm or parchment tube worm is a genus of marine polychaete worm that lives in a tube it constructs in sediments or attaches to a rocky or coral reef substrate .
Helianthus hirsutus is a North American species of sunflower known by the common name hairy sunflower .
Rhingia campestris is a species of hoverfly , 7 - -11 millimetres ( 0.3 - -0.4 in ) long , with a wingspan of 12 - -18 mm ( 0.5 - -0.7 in ) .
Lepidiolamprologus elongatus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers rocky areas .
Berberidopsis corallina is a species of ornamental plant .
Campylobacter rectus is a species of Campylobacter .
Apatosaurus ( meaning `` deceptive lizard '' /əˌpætəˈsɔːrəs/ ) is a genus of extinct sauropod dinosaurs that lived in North America during the Late Jurassic period .
Carinaria pseudorugosa is a species of sea gastropod , a holoplanktonic marine gastropod mollusk in the family Carinariidae .
Cycloramphus is a genus of frogs in the Cycloramphidae family .
Lupinus sericatus is a species of lupine known by the common name Cobb Mountain lupine .
Pterostylis banksii , commonly known as greenhood or tutukiwi , is an orchid species native to New Zealand .
Parhomaloptera microstoma is a species of balitorid or gastromyzontid loach endemic to the island of Borneo .
Megalocephalus ( meaning `` big head '' ) is an extinct genus of baphetid amphibian from the late Carboniferous of the British Isles .
Rutoceratidae is a family of prototypical nautilids , derived probably from either Brevicoceratidae or Acleistoceratidae of the order Oncocerida early in the Devonian .
Quercus margarettae , the sand post oak or dwarf post oak , is a North American species of oak in the beech family .
Allomyces neomoniliformis is a species of fungus from Japan .
Limnonectes nitidus ( common name : Tanah Rata wart frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Eburia cacapyra is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Ecuador .
Chrysolepis chrysophylla is a species of flowering plant in the beech family known by the common names golden chinquapin , giant chinquapin , and western chinquapin .
Astrophytum is a genus of six species of cacti , native to North America .
Phascolarctos ( from Ancient Greek phaskolos , referring to a pouch or bag , and arktos , meaning `` bear '' ) is a genus of marsupials containing only one extant species , the koala ( P. cinereus ) .
Uca tangeri is a species of fiddler crab that lives in the eastern Atlantic Ocean .
Batodonoides ( often misspelled as Batonoides ) is a genus of extinct shrew - like mammals , which includes a species that is possibly the smallest mammal to have ever lived .
Pycnanthemum is a genus of plants in the mint family ( Lamiaceae ) .
Hyloxalus edwardsi ( common name : Edwards ' rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Pitthea famula is a species of moth in the family Geometridae .
Isabelle 's ghost bat ( Diclidurus isabellus ) is a bat species found in northwestern Brazil , Guyana , and Venezuela , and possibly Colombia .
Cyphostemma juttae is a slow - growing succulent species of Cyphostemma from southern Africa , well known as an ornamental plant .
Finella geayi is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Scaliolidae .
Platorchestia is a genus of sand flea , containing the following species :
Trirachodon ( Greek : `` three ridge tooth '' ) is an extinct genus of tritylodontoid cynodont .
Penicillium kananaskense is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil of a forest in Alberta in Canada .
Quercus arkansana ( also called Arkansas oak ) is a species of plant in the beech family .
Desmazeria is a genus of Mediterranean plants in the grass family , related to Catapodium .
Acanthetaxalus bostrychoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acanthetaxalus .
Melarhaphe neritoides , common name : the small periwinkle , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
The tree species Sorbus americana ( syn . Pyrus americana ) is commonly known as the American mountain ash .
The Western Chinese mountain salamander or stream salamander ( Batrachuperis pinchonii ) is a species of hynobid salamander that is endemic to China .
Ivesia santolinoides is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common names silver mousetail , stellariopsis , Sierra mousetail and mousetail ivesia .
It contains the single species Hoplophrys oatesi , also known as the candy crab , Oates 's soft coral crab , commensal soft coral crab and Dendronephthya crab .
Tanganikallabes mortiauxi is a species of airbreathing catfish found in Burundi , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Tanzania , and Zambia .
Camissonia bairdii is a plant species endemic to Washington County , Utah .
Thelymitra pauciflora , commonly called the Slender Sun Orchid in Australia and Maikaika or Maika in New Zealand is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae .
Ancistrocarphus filagineus is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family , known by the common names woolly fishhooks and hooked groundstar .
Tondanichthys kottelati is a species of viviparous halfbeak endemic to Indonesia , where it is only known from Lake Tondano near Mount Tondano in the far north of the island of Sulawesi .
Ecsenius bandanus , known commonly as the Banda comb - tooth , Banda clown blenny , or the Banda combtooth - blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean .
Lestoideidae is a monotypic family of damselflies .
Septobasidium is a genus of Basidiomycota fungi .
Crataegus flabellata is a species of hawthorn known by the common name fanleaf hawthorn .
Callulops robustus ( commonly known as Boulenger 's callulops frog or robust frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Ancylostoma is a genus that includes some species of hookworm .
Teucrium gnaphalodes is a plant species in the genus Teucrium .
Astrapotheriidae is an extinct family of herbivorous South American land mammals that lived from the Late Eocene ( Mustersan SALMA ) to the Middle Miocene ( Laventan SALMA ) 37.8 to 15.97 million years ago .
Spaniocelyphus is a genus of beetle flies known from the Oriental ecozone .
Senecio velleioides , commonly known as forest groundsel , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae .
Limnonectes jarujini is a species of frog in the family Dicroglossidae , first described from near Kaeng Krachan Dam , Thailand .
Prismostictoides unihyala is a moth in the Endromidae family , and the only species in the genus Prismostictoides .
Branchiostomidae ( syn : Branchiostomatidae ) is the family that includes most of the lancelets , which are tiny chordates without a true spine but only a flexible notochord .
Lamprologus lethops is a species of cichlid fish from areas with fast current in the Congo River in Central Africa , where it is believed to live in depths as great as 160 metres ( 520 ft ) below the surface .
Psylla ( from the Greek psulla , meaning flea ) is a genus of sap - sucking insects belonging to the order Hemiptera .
Raillietia is a genus of mites placed in its own family , Railletiidae , in the order Mesostigmata .
Achyropappus is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1820 .
Axoclinus nigricaudus , known commonly as the Cortez triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny .
Azeca is a genus of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Cochlicopidae .
Cyclocheilichthys sinensis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Cyclocheilichthys .
Citharomantis falcata is a species of praying mantis native to Sumatra and Borneo .
Junggaria was a genus of rhyniophyte - like land plants known from fossils found in China in Upper Silurian strata ( Přídolí , around 430 to 420 million years ago ) .
Aphoenops delbreili is a species of beetle in the subfamily Trechinae .
Trachelipus sarmaticus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Ukraine .
Mecodema punctellum is a presumed - extinct species of ground beetle of the family Carabidae , endemic to Stephens Island in New Zealand .
Galium hallii ( Hall 's bedstraw ) is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae family .
Quercus castaneifolia , the chestnut - leaved oak , is a species of oak in the turkey oak section Quercus sect .
Cornulitida is an extinct order of encrusting animals from the Tentaculita class , which were common around the globe in the Ordovician to Devonian oceans , and survived until the Carboniferous .
Cornus sanguinea , the common dogwood , is a species of dogwood native to most of Europe and western Asia , occurring north to southern England and southern Scandinavia , and east to the Caspian Sea .
This species was originally noted and named in 1753 by Carolus Linnaeus as Agaricus campestris .
Streptomyces ascomycinicus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Kobe City in Japan .
The family Aplodontiidae also known as Aplodontidae , Haplodontiidae or Haploodontini is traditionaly clasified as the sole extant family of the suborder Protrogomorpha .
Discus ruderatus is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Discidae , the disk snails .
Acacia nanodealbata , known colloquially as dwarf silver - wattle , is a species of Acacia native to Australia .
Eleothreptus is a genus of nightjars in the Caprimulgidae family .
Cercocarpus breviflorus , commonly known as desert mountain mahogany or hairy mountain mahogany , is a species of plant in the rose family , native to northern Mexico and the southwestern United States .
Quercus graciliformis ( also called Chisos oak or slender oak ) is a rare North American species of trees in the beech family .
Chelyocarpus ulei is a species of palm tree that is native to the western Amazon .
Pseudophoenix ekmanii ( Cacheo , Cacheo de Oviedo , Dominican Cherry palm ) is a palm species endemic to the Barahona Peninsula and Isla Beata in the Dominican Republic .
In the east of its range the Kamchatka flounder overlaps with the range of the arrowtooth flounder , and similarities in appearance between the two species mean that they were not distinguished in commercial fishing until 2007 .
Polybia is a genus of eusocial wasps from South America ( Brazil , Argentina ) .
Junonia almana , the peacock pansy , is a species of nymphalid butterfly found in South Asia .
Plagiotremus iosodon is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific ocean .
Mycocepurus goeldii is a species of ant in the genus Mycocepurus .
Tamarix parviflora is a species of tamarisk known by the common name smallflower tamarisk .
Cervaphis quercus is an aphid species described by Takahashi in 1918 .
Abudefduf troschelii , the Pacific sergeant major or Panama sergeant major , is a species of damselfish belonging to the family Pomacentridae .
Hypsophrys nicaraguensis is a species of cichlid endemic to the Atlantic slope of Central America , from Nicaragua to Costa Rica .
Lichenochora is a genus of fungi in the order Phyllachorales .
Lethrinops longipinnis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is found at depths of 30 to 140 metres ( 98 to 459 ft ) ( usually only down to 70 metres ( 230 ft ) ) over sandy substrates .
Lioptilodes yungas is a species of moth in the genus Lioptilodes , known from Bolivia .
Eurymela fenestrata , widely known as the Common Jassid , is a species of leafhopper found throughout mainland Australia .
Leuciva , is a North American genus of plants in the sunflower family .
Araneus cinnabarinus , commonly known as the Falklands green spider is a species of orb - weaving spider endemic to the Falkland Islands as well as Chile , Argentina and the Juan Fernández Islands .
Pristobaeus jocosus is a species of spider in the jumping spider family ( Salticidae ) , found in Sulawesi .
Dasyatis ( Greek `` dasys '' meaning rough or dense and `` batus '' meaning skate ) is a genus of stingray .
Labeobarbus micronema is a species of cyprinid fish native to Cameroon and Gabon in Africa .
Salvia ballotiflora is a species of flowering plant in the mint family , Lamiaceae , that is native to Texas in the United States as well as northeastern and central Mexico .
Lythria purpuraria , the purple - barred yellow , is a species of moth of the family Geometridae .
Neobola is a genus of cyprinid fishes found mostly in East Africa .
Pseudocurimata is a genus of toothless characins found in tropical South America , with these currently described species :
Meconella oregana , the white fairypoppy , is a plant species native to Oregon , California , Washington and British Columbia .
Metacarcinus starri is an extinct species of crab in the family Cancridae , subfamily Cancrinae .
Prionosciadium bellii is a plant species endemic to the Mexican State of Michoacán .
Myopa dorsalis is a species belonging to the family Conopidae subfamily Myopinae .
Gyraulus costulatus is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Saurorictus is an extinct genus of Late Permian captorinid known from Western Cape Province of South Africa .
Gelyella is a genus of freshwater copepods which are `` surrounded by mystery '' .
Neoephemera antiqua is an extinct species of mayfly in the family Neoephemeridae that is known from early Eocene , Ypresian stage , lake deposits near the small community of Republic in Ferry County , Washington , USA .
Tryblidium reticulatum is an exctinct species of a paleozoic Silurian monoplacophoran .
Rosales is an order of flowering plants .
Origanum amanum ( Amanum oregano ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to the Hatay Province of southern Turkey , bordering on Syria .
Euarchontoglires ( synonymous with Supraprimates ) is a clade and a superorder of mammals , the living members of which belong to one of the five following groups : rodents , lagomorphs , treeshrews , colugos and primates ( including humans ) .
Trillium kurabayashii , the giant purple wakerobin , is a species of flowering plants native to southwestern Oregon and northern California .
Carpiodes is a genus of suckers found in freshtwater in North America .
Pachyrizodus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived from the Albian to the Campanian stage of the Early Cretaceous epoch .
Tympanopleura atronasus is a species of catfish of the family Auchenipteridae .
Handleyomys saturatior , also known as the cloud forest oryzomys or cloud forest rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Handleyomys of family Cricetidae .
Chenanisuchus ( `` Chenane crocodile '' ) is a genus of dyrosaurid crocodyliform from the Late Cretaceous of Mali and the Late Palaeocene of Sidi Chenane in Morocco .
Tarodes is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) , with the single species T. lineatus .
Lecanorineae are a suborder of pezizomycetes fungi , commonly known as the lichens and rostrate asci .
Orthotylus viridinervis is a species of green coloured bug from a family of Miridae that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Albania , Andorra , Croatia , Liechtenstein , Lithuania , Malta , Moldova , Portugal , Macedonia , and most part of Russia .
Agapanthia violacea is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Lamiinae .
Archaeospheniscus is an extinct genus of large penguins .
Hylomys is a small genus of the family Erinaceidae .
Morone is a genus of temperate basses native to the Atlantic coast of North America and the freshwater systems of the southwestern and eastern United States .
Euphorbia bombensis , commonly called the Southern Seaside Spurge , is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family .
Chaetodiadema japonicum is a species of sea urchins of the Family Diadematidae .
Sinezona iota is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Scissurellidae .
Neottia banksiana is a species of orchid known by the common name northwestern twayblade .
Urceolina is a genus of South American plants in the Amaryllis family , all native to Perú .
Evolenes exarata is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Evolenes .
Berberis aetnensis is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1826 .
Dipturus nidarosiensis , commonly known as the Norwegian skate or black skate , is a species of skate found in the Norwegian Sea , North Sea and the Bay of Biscay .
Vaccinium tenellum , the small black blueberry , is a plant species native to the southeastern United States from southeastern Mississippi to northern Florida to southern Virginia .
Peltobatrachus ( from Greek pelte , meaning shield and batrakhos , meaning frog ) is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the late Permian period of Tanzania .
Palleon nasus , commonly known as the elongate leaf chameleon , is a species of chameleon endemic to Madagascar .
Agasicles hygrophila is a species of leaf beetle known by the common name alligator weed flea beetle .
Maimetsha arctica is an extinct genus of wasp which existed during the Cretaceous period , and the only species in the genus Maimetsha .
Shinkailepas kaikatensis is a species of sea snail , a false limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phenacolepadidae .
The Plagiorchiata are by far the largest suborder of plagiorchiidan flatworms .
Collodictyon is a basal genus of single - celled eukaryotes not closely related to any heretofore known kingdom of that domain .
Campanula raineri ( Rainer 's bellflower , Rainer 's harebell ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Campanula of the family Campanulaceae , native to the Swiss and Italian Alps .
Phenacodontidae is an extinct family of large herbivorous mammals traditionally placed in the wastebasket taxon Condylarthra , that may represent early perissodactyls .
Neothais marginatra , common name : the brownish drupe , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Penicillium sacculum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces the xanthone 1-hydroxy-3-methoxy-6-sulfo-8-methylxanthone .
Solariella lacunella , common name the channelled solarielle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Balanoglossus is an ocean - dwelling acorn worm ( Enteropneusta ) genus of great zoological interest because , being a Hemichordate , it is an `` evolutionary link '' between invertebrates and vertebrates .
Dinoponera snellingi ( named after Roy Snelling ) is a queenless species of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Amanita breckonii is a species of agaric fungus in the large genus Amanita .
Lagosuchus is a genus of small archosaur from the middle Triassic period .
Zeargyrodes fasciatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Zeargyrodes .
Ginkgo biloba , known as ginkgo or as the maidenhair tree , is the only living species in the division Ginkgophyta , all others being extinct .
Aulotandra is a genus of plants native to Cameroon and Madagascar .
Oncidium klotzschianum is a species of orchid occurring from Costa Rica to Peru and Venezuela .
Geniostoma confertiflorum is a species of plant in the Loganiaceae family endemic to Fiji .
Carya washingtonensis is an extinct species of hickory nut in the walnut family Juglandaceae .
Erica ciliaris is a species of heather , known in the British Isles as Dorset heath .
Michaelophorus margaritae is a species of moth in the genus Michaelophorus , known from Ecuador .
Oberea adumbrata is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Tippman in 1958 .
Luzocephalus is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Early Triassic of Russia .
Sinobdella sinensis is a species of the spiny eel family ( order Synbranchiformes ) , and is the only species of the genus Sinobdella .
Dikerogammarus haemobaphes is a species of freshwater gammarid crustacean .
Ugrunaaluk is a genus of saurolophine hadrosaurid which was found in the Arctic of Alaska .
Musa lolodensis is a species of wild banana ( genus Musa ) , occurring naturally from the Moluccas through to New Guinea .
Priabona is an extinct genus of big - headed flies in the dipteran subfamily Nephrocerinae , within which it is one of only two genera .
Desisella strandiella is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Desisella .
The Santa Marta sabrewing ( Campylopterus phainopeplus ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Aetosaurus is an extinct genus of archosaur reptile belonging to the order Aetosauria .
Lycia ursaria , the stout spanworm moth or bear , is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Caladenia discoidea , commonly known as the dancing spider orchid , antelope orchid or bee orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Caenis amica is a species of mayfly in the genus Caenis .
Cicindela patruela , commonly known as Northern Barrens Tiger Beetle is a species of tiger beetle from the Cicindelinae subfamily .
Shorea balanocarpoides ( also called White Meranti or Yellow Meranti ) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Poteria translucida is a species of tropical land snail with gills and an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Neocyclotidae .
Euhadra quaesita , common name , the sought - after false hadra , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Bradybaenidae .
Huanansaurus is an extinct genus of oviraptorid dinosaur that lived approximately 72 million years ago , between the Campanian and Maastrichtian , during the latter part of the Cretaceous period in what is now China , in the Nanxiong Formation .
Ancharius griseus is a species of catfish of family Anchariidae .
Salix koriyanagi is a species of willow native to Korea .
The Tritoniidae are a taxonomic family of dendronotid nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod molluscs .
Taracus is a genus of harvestman , or Opiliones , typically found living in caves in the United States .
Micryletta is a small genus of microhylid frogs .
Herpetogaster is an extinct monotypic genus of animal from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale containing the species Herpetogaster collinsi .
Sternbergia schubertii is a rare and quite possibly extinct plant species known only from one specimen collected in Izmir , Turkey , in 1839 .
Uroderma is a genus of Central and South American phyllostomid bats .
Thylacares is a genus of Thylacocephalan containing only the single species Thylacares brandonensis .
Livonia mammilla , common name False melon or False baler , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk of the genus Livonia in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Conus coronatus , common name the crowned cone or the coronated cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Larinia is an orb - weaving spider genus .
Arta statalis , the posturing arta moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Arta .
Lysmata vittata is a species of shrimp , native to the Indo - Pacific from East Africa to the Philippines , Japan , Australia and New Zealand .
Lypusa is a genus of moths of the Lypusidae family , traditionally held to be a monotypic lineage of Tineoidea .
Mylia taylorii , the Taylor 's flapwort , is a species of leafy liverwort .
Incilius tacanensis ( common name : Volcan Tacana toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Cypripedium molle is a species of orchid native to Puebla and Oaxaca , Mexico .
Pseudochalceus is a genus of characins from freshwater habitats in western Ecuador and western Colombia .
Vernonieae is a tribe of about 1300 species of plants in the aster family .
Athous apfelbecki is a species of click beetle from Elateridae family .
Ficus daimingshanensis is a plant species native to the Chinese provinces of Guangxi and Hunan .
Altica oleracea is a species of leaf beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae , subfamily Galerucinae .
Psychristus belkab is a species of ground beetle from the Harpalinae subfamily that is endemic to Yunnan province of China .
Spilosoma virginica is a species of moth in the Arctiinae subfamily .
Drosophila lanaiensis was a species of fly in family Drosophilidae that was endemic to Hawaii .
Boechera falcatoria ( formerly Arabis falcatoria ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Grouse Creek rockcress .
Ergot ( pron . /ɜrɡət/ UR - gut ) or ergot fungi refers to a group of fungi of the genus Claviceps .
Ascophyllum nodosum is a large , common brown alga ( Phaeophyceae ) in the family Fucaceae , being the only species in the genus Ascophyllum .
Siphopteron quadrispinosum is a species of small sea slug , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusc in the order Cephalaspidea , the headshield slugs .
Anostomus anostomus , also known as the striped headstander , striped anostomus , and striped anastomus , is a species of fish .
Hazardia cana is a rare North American species of shrubs in the daisy family known by the common names Guadalupe hazardia , San Clemente Island hazardia , or simply island hazardia .
Gersemia rubiformis , commonly known as the sea strawberry , is a species of soft coral in the family Nephtheidae .
Canis ferox ( Latin : canis : dog , ferox : fierce ; hence fierce dog ) is a species of canidae which was endemic to North America and lived from the Late Hemphillian stage ( 10.9 Mya ) of the Pliocene through the Miocene epoch ( 5.8 Mya ) .
Tephrosia candida , the white hoarypea , is a species of plant in the legume family .
Allium chrysonemum is a species of onions native the Sierra de Cazorla mountain range in southeastern Spain .
Delphinium viridescens is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common name Wenatchee larkspur .
Anoura is a genus of leaf - nosed bats from Central and South America .
Clavatula taxea , common name the yew turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae .
Pourouma cecropiifolia ( Amazon Grape , Amazon Tree - grape or Uvilla ; syn . P. multifida ) is a species of Pourouma , native to tropical South America , in the western Amazon Basin in northern Bolivia , western Brazil , southeastern Colombia , eastern Ecuador , eastern Peru , and southern Venezuela .
Cteniloricaria maculata is a species of armored catfish native to French Guiana and Suriname where it is found in the Maroni and Corantijn River basins .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pectinotrichum llanense .
Hipposyngnathus is an extinct genus of prehistoric ray - finned fish that lived during the early Oligocene epoch .
Pericopsis elata , the African teak , afromosia , or afrormosia , is a species of flowering plant in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Astralium rotularium , common name the rotary star shell or the knob star shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Perny 's long - nosed squirrel ( Dremomys pernyi ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Helix godetiana is a species of large , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
Muhlenbergia glomerata is a species of grass known by the common names spiked muhly and marsh muhly .
It is the only species remaining in the monotypic genus Pelvetia .
Neocyprideis timorensis is a species of Indo - Pacific ostracod that has existed since the Miocene .
The Centrocnemidinae are a subfamily of the reduviid ( assassin bugs ) , found exclusively on tree trunks , where their bodies camouflage well .
Amantis hainanensis is a species of praying mantis native to China and Vietnam .
Upeneichthys is a genus of goatfishes native to the Indian and Pacific coasts of Australia .
Lasiancistrus saetiger is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil .
The Papuan king parrot ( Alisterus chloropterus ) , also known as the green - winged king parrot , is a species of parrot in the Psittaculidae family found in West Papua and Papua New Guinea .
Ageratina luciae - brauniae is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Lucy Braun 's snakeroot and rockhouse white snakeroot .
Cymopterus deserticola is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names desert cymopterus or desert springparsley .
Symphoricarpos hesperius , called the trailing snowberry or creeping snowberry , is a North American species of trailing shrubs in the honeysuckle family .
Philaenus is a genus of insects belonging to the family Aphrophoridae , the spittlebugs .
Paphiopedilum kolopakingii is a species of orchid endemic to Borneo ( central Kalimantan ) .
Amblypygi is an order of arachnid chelicerate arthropods also known as whip spiders and tailless whip scorpions ( not to be confused with whip scorpions and vinegaroons that belong to the related order Thelyphonida ) .
Veleropilina zografi is a Recent deep - sea ( bathyal ) species of monoplacophoran , a superficially limpet - like marine mollusk from the Atlantic Ocean .
Cryptandra tomentosa , commonly known as Prickly Cryptandra , is a shrub species in the Buckthorn family , Rhamnaceae .
Blenniella cyanostigma , the Striped rockskipeer , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Indian Ocean .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Hidakaea tumidula .
Eleutherodactylus rhodesi ( common name : Rhodes ' robber frog ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Phalaenopsis philippinensis is an endemic species of orchid found from Luzon island in the Philippines .
Clasmodosaurus was a genus of dinosaur , probably a sauropod .
Acanthopleura gemmata , the Jewelled Chiton , is a species of chiton .
