Dactylotum bicolor , also known as the rainbow grasshopper , painted grasshopper , or the barber pole grasshopper , is a species of grasshopper in the family Acrididae .
Gelasinospora is a genus of fungi within the order Sordariales .
Crotalaria juncea , reduced both the germination and seedlings of various crop species ( bell pepper , tomato , onion , and others ) .
The Zanzibar red colobus ( Procolobus kirkii ) is a species of red colobus monkey endemic to Unguja , the main island of the Zanzibar Archipelago , off the coast of Tanzania .
Rotaria is a genus of asexual microorganism known as a bdelloid rotifer .
It is known only from the fossil remains of a single species , the huge and presumably flightless Eremopezus eocaenus .
The Leptotyphlopidae ( commonly called slender blind snakes or thread snakes ) are a family of snakes found in North and South America , Africa , and Asia .
Abricta is a genus of cicada found in Réunion , Mauritius , northeastern India , the Moluccas , New Caledonia and eastern Australia .
Macrotomoxia palpalis is a species of beetle in the Macrotomoxia genus that is in the Mordellidae family , which is a part of the Tenebrionoidea superfamily .
Strumigenys lyroessa is a species of ant found in Bhutan , India , and Sri Lanka .
Erigeron greenei is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Greene 's narrow - leaved daisy .
Pegomastax ( `` strong jaw '' ) is a genus of heterodontosaurid dinosaur discovered in Lower Jurassic rocks in South Africa .
Charales is an order of freshwater green algae in the division Charophyta commonly known as `` stoneworts '' .
Lathyrus linifolius is a species of pea , commonly called bitter vetch or heath pea .
Aloe africana ( known as the African Aloe ) is an arborescent species of aloe plant , indigenous to the Eastern Cape Province , South Africa .
Paramoeba is a genus of common parasites , including species that can cause infection in fish , crabs ( including the `` blue crab '' , Callinectes sapidus ) , sea urchins and others .
Meiacanthus urostigma is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern Indian Ocean where it is only known from the Surin Islands .
Asclepias subulata is a species of milkweed known commonly as the rush milkweed , desert milkweed or ajamete .
Colus stimpsoni , common name the Stimpson 's colus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Urodacus yaschenkoi , commonly known as the inland robust scorpion , is a species of scorpion belonging to the subfamily Urodacinae ( family Scorpionidae ) .
The Florida grasshopper sparrow is one of four subspecies of grasshopper sparrows in North America .
Diaphorodoris luteocincta is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusc in the family Calycidorididae .
Longipterygidae is a family of early enantiornithine birds from the early Cretaceous Period of China .
Lipocarpha occidentalis , the Western halfchaff sedge , or Pacific halfchaff sedge , is a plant species native to western part of the United States but cultivated as an ornamental in other regions .
Chaenactis cusickii is a North American species of flowering plants in the aster family known by the common name Morning brides or Cusick 's pincushion .
Popillia is a genus of scarab beetles .
Cerithium caeruleum , the Cerith Sand Snail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cerithiidae .
Ogygioses eurata is a species of moth of the Palaeosetidae family .
Holapogon maximus also known as the Titan cardinalfish , is a species in the family Apogonidae , the cardinalfishes .
Dibamus nicobaricum is a species of lizard found in the Nicobar Islands of India .
Allium hookeri is a plant species native to India , Sri Lanka , Myanmar ( Burma ) , Bhutan , and southwestern China ( Sichuan , Tibet and Yunnan ) .
Trifolium nigrescens , the small white clover , is an annual species which is widespread around the Mediterranean , including north Africa , and the Middle East .
The Spine - tufted Skimmer , or Crimson - tailed Marsh Hawk , Brown - backed Red Marsh Hawk , ( Orthetrum chrysis ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Eurygaster confidens is a species of true bug or shield - backed bug belonging to the family Scutelleridae .
Liocarcinus is a genus of crabs , which includes the flying crab , the vernal crab and several other swimming crabs .
Sebastes schlegelii also known as the Korean rockfish , is a predatory species of seaperch found in northern Asia .
Austrofusus glans is a species of medium - sized sea snail or whelk , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Lumbricus terrestris is a large , reddish worm species widely distributed around the world ( along with several other lumbricids ) .
Vitis ficifolia is a species of liana in the grape family native to the Asian temperate climate zone .
Atlantidae is a family of sea snails , holoplanktonic gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Betasuchus is a genus of theropod dinosaur which lived during the Late Cretaceous Period .
Ruehleia is a genus of sauropodomorph dinosaur from the Late Triassic period of Germany .
In a study on its effects on fungus , Asarum caudatum had antifungal properties when tested against nine fungal species .
Alphatetraviridae is a family of viruses .
Cattleya nobilior ( literally `` the More Noble Cattleya '' , referring to the flowers which are larger than those of C. walkeriana , the other rhizanthoid Cattleya , of which it was originally considered a variety ) is a species of orchid .
The Belladonna Cracker ( Hamadryas belladonna ) is a species of cracker butterfly in the family Nymphalidae .
Dasypus bellus , the beautiful armadillo , is an extinct armadillo species endemic to North America and South America from the Pleistocene , living from 1.8 mya--11,000 years ago , existing for approximately 1.789 million years .
Microseris acuminata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Sierra foothill silverpuffs .
Morchella spongiola is a species of fungus in the Morchellaceae family .
Tradescantia buckleyi , commonly known as Buckley 's spiderwort , is a species of flowering plant in the dayflower family , Commelinaceae .
Astragalus congdonii is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Congdon 's milkvetch .
Canarium mutabile , common name the variable stromb , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Alfaroa williamsii is a tropical monoecious cloud forest dwelling species of tree first recognized in the Cordillera Central of Nicaragua at an altitude of 1.3 km . The mature tree is 15 - 25 m in height , with a 0.5 m DBH .
Passiflora citrina is a species of Passion flower native to Central America .
Armodorum is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to Southeast Asia .
Salticus peckhamae is a species of spider from a Salticidae family .
Machaerirhynchus is a genus of passerine birds with affinities to woodswallows and butcherbirds .
Nuclearia is a nucleariid genus .
The genus Aztekium contains three species of small globular cactus .
Arctotis fastuosa , called Monarch - of - the - veld , is a species of African plants in the daisy family , native to Namibia and South Africa .
Aeluroidea is an extant superfamily of feline - like carnivores that are , or were , endemic to North America , South America , Africa , and Asia .
Schoepfiaceae is a family of flowering plants recognized in the APG III system of 2009 .
Erianthemum dregei is a species of parasitic plant in the Loranthaceae family , and is commonly known as the Hairy mistletoe or Wood flower .
Appedesis vidua is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Appedesis .
Malacothrix clevelandii is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Cleveland 's desertdandelion .
Lepidurus packardi is a rare species of tadpole shrimp known by the common name vernal pool tadpole shrimp .
Navarretia subuligera is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names awl - leaf pincushionplant or awl - leaved navarretia .
Megapenthes lugens is a species of primarily European click beetle .
Carex longebrachiata , commonly known as Australian sedge or drooping sedge , is a plant species in the sedge family , Cyperaceae .
Paressonodon is an extinct genus of multituberculate which existed in Colorado during the late Cretaceous period .
Noguerornis is a genus of enantiornithine bird possibly related to Iberomesornis .
Prionus coriarius ( sometimes referred to as `` the tanner '' or `` the sawyer '' ) is a species of longhorn beetle .
Tachina brevicornis is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that can be found in China , Japan , and Russia .
The genus includes one species , Rooneyia viejaensis .
Francisella tularensis is a pathogenic species of Gram - negative , rod - shaped coccobacillus , an aerobe bacterium .
Micraspis flavovittata is a species of ladybird of the genus Micraspis .
The Adelaide pygmy blue - tongue skink or pygmy bluetongue ( Tiliqua adelaidensis ) is a species of skink in the Scincidae family .
Erythroxylum rufum , the rufous false cocaine , is a flowering plant species in the genus Erythroxylum .
Leptotila is a genus of birds in the family Columbidae .
Pulmonaria angustifolia ( narrow - leaved lungwort , blue cowslip ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Boraginaceae , native to central and north eastern Europe .
Geragnostus is a genus of very small agnostid trilobites whose fossils are found Ordovician - aged marine strata from Eurasia , North America and Argentina .
The Antilocapridae are a family of artiodactyls endemic to North America .
Proentelodon is an extinct genus of entelodont artiodactyl from the Middle Eocene of Mongolia .
Cicindela circumpicta , also known as Habroscelimorpha circumpicta , is a species of a tiger beetles in the Cicindelidae family .
Alosa agone is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alosa .
The D'Orbigny 's Banded Anole , Pristidactylus fasciatus , is a species of lizard from Chile and Argentina .
Cyathea hancockii is a species of tree fern native to the Ryukyu Islands , Japan , Taiwan and Hong Kong .
Brissopsis atlantica is a species of sea urchin of the Family Brissidae .
Microsynodontis laevigata is a species of upside - down catfish endmic to Gabon where it is found in the Ivindo River .
Egglestonichthys is a genus of gobies native to brackish and marine waters of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Altijuba is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing one species Altijuba oktediensis , which is known from Papua New Guinea .
Hypsopygia thymetusalis , the spruce needleworm moth or paler dolichomia moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Hypsopygia .
Haploferonia simplex is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Haploferonia .
Coltivirus is a genus of viruses ( belonging to the Reoviridae family ) that infects vertebrates , invertebrates , and plants .
Amphiesma deschauenseei , commonly known as the northern keelback or Deschauensee 's keelback , is a species of nonvenomous natricine snake endemic to Asia .
Scabiosa caucasica , the Caucasian pincushion flower , pincushion - flower or Caucasian scabious , is a species of flowering plant in the family Caprifoliaceae , native to the Caucasus , north eastern Turkey , and northern Iran .
Antennaria parvifolia is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Nuttall 's pussytoes and small - leaf pussytoes ( not to be confused with littleleaf pussytoes ) .
Lycodon gammiei , commonly known as Gammie 's wolf snake , is a species of nonvenomous colubrid endemic to northern India .
Guadalupiidae is a family of fossil sponges that lived from the Pennsylvanian ( Carboniferous ) until the Norian ( Late Triassic ) .
Gouania vitifolia ( also known as Oʻahu chewstick ) is an endangered species flowering plant in the buckthorn family , Rhamnaceae that is endemic to Hawaii .
Reganochromis calliurus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika in East Africa where it can be found in deeper coastal waters over sandy substrates at depths of around 60 metres ( 200 ft ) .
Hardenbergia is a small genus of leguminous vines from Australia .
The sole species , Woollsia pungens , is a small shrub found in eastern Australia , from Pigeon House Mountain in southern New South Wales north into Queensland .
Ablepharus budaki , commonly known as Budak 's snake - eyed skink , is a species of skink endemic to the Near East .
Paraoxypilus is a genus of mantis , known as the boxer bark mantids .
Allium baluchistanicum is a plant species endemic to the Baluchistan region in Pakistan .
Culoptila is a genus of caddisflies found primarily in Central America as well as the United States .
Lyonia ligustrina is a species of flowering plant in the heath family known by the common names maleberry and he - huckleberry .
Phlox caespitosa is a species of phlox known by the common name tufted phlox .
Hylophorbus ( Mawatta Frogs ) is a genus of microhylid frogs endemic to New Guinea .
Calotes bachae is a species of lizard in the Agamidae family .
Vibrio casei is a Gram - negative species of bacterium in the genus Vibrio .
Deinandra increscens is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name grassland tarweed .
Izumonauta is an extinct genus of shelled octopods from the Mid to Late Miocene of Japan and New Zealand .
Gilia cana is used as an exclusive food plant by the larvae of the Lepidoptera species Schinia biundulata .
Snyderina is a genus of waspfishes found in the western Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Dendropsophus leucophyllatus ( common names : Beireis ' treefrog , also white - leaf frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Leptotyphlops nasalis , or Taylor 's blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Oreokera is a genus of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Punctoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Schistura oedipus is a species of troglobitic stone loach endemic to Thailand .
Clea cambojiensis is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks , most of which are marine .
Prenoceratops , ( meaning ' bent or prone - horned face ' and derived from Greek prene-/πρηνη- meaning ' bent forwards ' or ' prone ' , cerat-/κερατ- meaning ' horn ' and -ops/ωψ meaning ' face ' ) is a genus of ceratopsian dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous Period .
Ulva prolifera is a species of seaweed in Ulvaceae family that can be found worldwide .
Thyrsostachys is a genus of Chinese and Indochinese bamboo in the grass family .
Rana iriodes is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that is endemic to Vietnam .
Palaeospinax is an extinct genus of shark which lived from the Early Triassic to the end of the Eocene epoch .
Lyonia fruticosa , the poor - grub or coastal plain staggerbush , is a plant species native to the US states of Florida , southern Georgia and the extreme southern part of South Carolina .
Heteroponera flava is a species of ant in the genus Heteroponera .
Neohecyra graueri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neohecyra .
Dothideales are an order of bitunicate fungi consisting mainly of saprobic or plant parasitic species .
Puncha ratzeburgi is a species of snakeflies in the family Raphidiidae .
Aethes dilucidana , the short - barred yellow conch , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Euprymna berryi , commonly called humming - bird bobtail squid or Berry 's bobtail squid among various other vernacular names , is a species of mollusc cephalopod in the family Sepiolidae .
Cantharidus pulcherrimus , common name the beautiful jewel top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Dorstenia contrajerva is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Mexico , Central America , the Caribbean and South America .
Mallosia graeca is a species of beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , that can be found only in Greece .
Typhlichthys subterraneus is a species of fish in the Amblyopsidae family endemic to karst regions of the eastern United States .
Eupatorium tashiroi is a plant species in Asteraceae .
Tillandsia lotteae is a species of flowering plant from the genus Tillandsia .
Taxus chinensis is a species of yew .
Ocenebra erinaceus , common name the European sting winkle , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex and rock snails .
Mycena nargan , commonly known as the Nargan 's bonnet , is a species of fungus in the Mycenaceae family , and the sole member of the section Nargan in the genus Mycena .
Leptotyphlops melanotermus , or the Latin American blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Sotoa is a genus of orchid , a relatively new genus described in 2010 .
Austromorium hetericki is an Australian species of ant in the genus Austromorium .
Bossiaea obcordata , commonly known as spiny bossiaea , is a plant species in the family Fabaceae .
Aphanotorulus ammophilus , also known as the Black spotted pleco or L094 , is a species of benthopelagic tropical freshwater catfish in the family Loricariidae endemic to Venezuela , specifically the Río Orinoco drainage .
Abraeus is a genus of hister beetles .
Libinia dubia , the longnose spider crab , is a species of crab in the family Epialtidae .
Flabellina llerae is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine heterobranchia mollusc in the family Flabellinidae .
Burnettia , common name lizard orchid , is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Boltonia apalachicolensis , common name Apalachicola doll's - daisy , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Heterandria is a genus of livebearing fishes within the family Poeciliidae .
Cranoglanis multiradiatus is a species of armorhead catfish found in China with questionable records from Vietnam .
Trachelipus difficilis is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Hungary , Romania and Slovakia .
Agonum darlingtoni is a species of ground beetle from Platyninae subfamily , that can be found in the United States .
It contains only one species , Aepylopha thalassia , which is found in Australia .
Olybria furciferella is a species of snout moth in the genus Olybria .
Scartella itajobi is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Atlantic ocean .
Inocarpus fagifer , commonly known as the Tahitian Chestnut , Polynesian Chestnut , Aila or Mape tree , is a species of flowering plant in the subfamily Faboideae of the legume family , Fabaceae .
Amaranthus torreyi is a species of flowering plant that is sometimes considered to be a synonym of Amaranthus watsonii .
Rhinocricidae is a family of millipedes , that occurs disjunctly in Malesia and neighbouring parts of Australasia and in the Neotropics .
Moghreberia is an extinct genus of dicynodont from the Triassic period in Morocco .
Tetralonia commixtana , also known as Tetralonia ( Thygatina ) commixtana , is a species of bees belonging to the family Apidae subfamily Apinae .
Leiocassis is a genus of bagrid catfishes found mostly in Southeast Asia with some species occurring in China .
Leptopelis is a genus of frogs found throughout Africa .
Xiphasia setifer , the hairtail blenny or the snake blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Kerguelenella innominata is a species of air - breathing sea snail , a false limpet , a marine pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Siphonariidae , the false limpets .
Dendropsophus koechlini is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , known commonly as Koechlin 's Treefrog .
Gammarus hyalelloides is a species of amphipod crustacean in the family Gammaridae .
Aptostichus simus is a species of trapdoor spider in the family Euctenizidae .
Distenia is a genus of Disteniid beetle .
Alocasia cucullata is a species of flowering plant in the arum family known by the common names Chinese taro , Chinese ape , Buddha 's hand , and hooded dwarf elephant ear .
Discocactus is a genus of tropical cactus .
Procaimanoidea ( `` Before Caiman - forms '' ) is an extinct genus of alligatorid from the Eocene of North America .
Pituophis is a genus of nonvenomous colubrid snakes commonly referred to as gopher snakes , pine snakes , and bull snakes , which are endemic to North America .
Limax ecarinatus ( also known as Limacus maculatus when the subgenus Limacus is elevated to the generic level ) , is a large species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Limacidae , the keelback slugs .
Jiangjunosaurus is a genus of herbivorous stegosaurian dinosaur from the Oxfordian - age ( Upper Jurassic ) Shishugou Formation of the Junggar Basin , Xinjiang , China .
The Typhlopidae are a family of blind snakes .
Flabellina marcusorum , ( Spanish common name : Eolidáceo de Marcus ) is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Flabellinidae .
Vermilacinia cerebra is classified in the subgenus Cylindricaria in which it is distinguished from related species by the thallus divided into tubular inflated or somewhat compressed fan - shaped branches .
Arytropteris pondo , known as Pondo Flat - necked Shieldback , is a species of shield - backed katydid .
Boechera hoffmannii ( formerly Arabis hoffmannii ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Hoffmann 's rockcress .
Packera macounii is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Siskiyou Mountains ragwort .
Sievekingia is a genus of orchid , comprising 20 species found in Central and South America , from Nicaragua east to the Guianas and south to Bolivia .
Zabrus morio is a species of ground beetle in the Pterostichinae subfamily that can be found in such Asian countries as Afghanistan , Armenia , Georgia , Iran , Kazakhstan , Pakistan , Syria , Turkmenistan , Turkey and Uzbekistan .
Acanthostega ( meaning spiny roof ) is an extinct genus of stem - tetrapod , among the first vertebrate animals to have recognizable limbs .
Knipowitschia mermere is a species of fresh water goby endemic to Lake Marmara in Turkey where it can be found in shallow , poorly oxygenated water with plentiful weed growth .
Erodium moschatum is a species of flowering plant in the geranium family known by the common names musk stork's - bill and whitestem filaree .
Chlorogalum purpureum is a species of flowering plant related to the agaves known by the common name purple amole .
Mimotragocephala dujardini is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimotragocephala .
The Tremellomycetes are a class of dimorphic fungi .
Omphalota chlorobasis is a species of snout moth in the genus Omphalota .
Orthosiphon aristatus is a plant species in the family of Lamiaceae / Labiatae .
Chthonerpeton indistinctum is a species of amphibian in the Typhlonectidae family found in Argentina , Brazil , Paraguay , and Uruguay .
Dunaliella is a genus of the algae family Dunaliellaceae .
Agrostis elliottiana is a species of grass known by the common name Elliott 's bent grass .
Crepis bakeri is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Baker 's hawksbeard .
Litadeini is a pan - tropical tribe of lace bugs .
Pseudocyriocrates strandi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudocyriocrates .
Paracirrhites is a genus of hawkfishes found on tropical reefs of the Indian Ocean and Pacific Ocean .
Isocoma arguta is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Carquinez goldenbush .
The single described species Pseudopartona ornata is only found in French Guiana .
Palaeoaplysina is a genus of tabular , calcified fossils that are a component of many Late Palaeozoic reefs .
Conus wallangra , common name the Wallangra cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Opades costipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Opades .
Bakerella is genus of sixteen showy mistletoe species in Madagascar and the Mascarenes .
Combresomyces is a genus of hyphal , parasitic oomycete known from the fossil record ; it infects organisms such as the seed fern Lyginopteris .
Chlorurus sordidus , known commonly as the daisy parrotfish or bullethead parrotfish , is a species of marine fish in the family Scaridae .
Antedon mediterranea is a species of stalkless crinoid in the family Antedonidae , commonly known as the Mediterranean feather star .
Milvus is a genus of medium - sized birds of prey .
Potomotyphlus kaupii is a species of amphibian in the Typhlonectidae family .
Boophis tephraeomystax is a species of frog in the Mantellidae family endemic to Madagascar .
Raorchestes chalazodes ( chalazodes bubble - nest frog , white - spotted bush frog , or Günther 's bush frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Fissurella costata , common name : the costate keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Ribes nevadense ( sometimes spelled R. nevadaense ) is a species of currant known by the common names Sierra currant and mountain pink currant .
Glossostelma is a plant genus in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1895 .
Enoplosus armatus , the old wife ( plural : old wives ) , is a species of perciform fish endemic to the temperate coastal waters of Australia .
Cheirolophus is a genus in the sunflower family described as a genus in 1827 .
Granulenotes granulipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Granulenotes .
Gryllus assimilis , commonly known as the Jamaican field cricket , is one of many cricket species known as a field cricket .
Papilio fuelleborni is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Tanzania and Malawi .
Oectoperodes rufitinctalis is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Oectoperodes .
Eriogonum saxatile is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name hoary buckwheat .
Janthina globosa is a species of holoplanktonic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Janthinidae , the violet snails or purple storm snails .
Leucoptera spartifoliella is a species of moth in family Lyonetiidae known by the common name Scotch broom twig miner .
Alcithoe hedleyi is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Iapetognathus fluctivagus is a species of denticulate cordylodan conodonts belonging to the genus Iapetognathus .
Hybopsis is a genus of cyprinid fish endemic to the United States .
Thor amboinensis , commonly known as the squat shrimp or sexy shrimp , is a species of shrimp found across the Indo - West Pacific and in parts of the Atlantic Ocean .
Spasskia brevicarinata is a species of parasitoid wasp native to the Guizhou and Yunnan provinces of China .
Apistobuthus pterygocercus is a species of scorpion that lives on the Arabian Peninsula .
Camponotus eastwoodi is a species of ant in the genus Camponotus .
Acer pauciflorum is an Asian species of maple in the sandalwood family .
Populus guzmanantlensis is a species of plant in the family Salicaceae .
Allium speculae , the Little River Canyon Onion , is a plant species native to the US States of Georgia and Alabama , especially in the vicinity of the Little River Canyon National Preserve in northeastern Alabama .
Manfreda virginica , commonly known as the false aloe , rattlesnake master , and Virginia agave , is a species of flowering plant related to agaves .
Astragalus obscurus is a species of milkvetch known by the common name arcane milkvetch .
The Jamaican monkey ( Xenothrix mcgregori ) is an extinct species of New World monkey first uncovered at Long Mile Cave in Jamaica by Harold Anthony in 1919 .
The binni , or Mesopotamic Barbel , Mesopotamichthys sharpeyi , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Tigris - Euphrates river system .
Alvaradoa is a genus of plant in family Picramniaceae .
Melica stricta is a species of grass known by the common name rock melic .
The genus contains a single described species , Haidomyrmodes mammuthus .
Austriadraco is a genus of pterosaur living during the Late Triassic in the area of present Austria .
Valvata virens is a species of freshwater snail in the family Valvatidae .
Mahonia hancockiana is a species of flowering plant in the family Berberidaceae , first described in 1917 .
Aristolochia quangbinhensis ( ( Vietnamese ) Phòng Kỷ Quảng Bình ) is a Endemic Flora species in Aristolochia genus .
Tieghemella heckelii ( also called Baku or Cherry Mahogany ) is a tree species of the genus Tieghemella in the plant family of the Sapotaceae .
Colubraria testacea is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colubrariidae .
Miathyria is a Neotropical genus of dragonflies .
Achondrostoma oligolepis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Achondrostoma .
The Alcyonacea , or soft corals , are an order of corals which do not produce calcium carbonate skeletons .
Australosuchus is an extinct genus of crocodylian belonging to the subfamily Mekosuchinae .
Oreorchis patens is a species of orchid native to eastern Asia .
Uroplectes formosus is a species of scorpion in the family Buthidae , and the smallest species in the genus Uroplectes .
Habenaria medusa is a species of orchid endemic to Java , Sumatra , Sulawesi and Borneo .
Aggiosaurus is an extinct genus of geosaurine metriorhynchid crocodyliform known from the Late Jurassic ( late Oxfordian stage ) of Nice , southeastern France .
Sinocyclocheilus tileihornes is a species of freshwater ray - finned fish in the genus Sinocyclocheilus .
Myelodes jansei is a species of snout moth , and the type species in the genus Myelodes .
Hepsetus is a genus of African fishes , the African pikes , in the order Characiformes .
Pararhadinorhynchus mugilis is a species of parasitic worm in the phylum Acanthocephala .
Aspistomella lobioptera is a species of ulidiidae or picture - winged fly in the genus Aspistomella of the family Ulidiidae .
Pitekunsaurus is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of Neuquén , Argentina .
Rhammatophyllum pachyrhizum is a plant species native to Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan .

Carlephyton madagascariense is a plant species in the genus Carlephyton endemic to Madagascar .
Horsfordia is a small genus of flowering plants in the mallow family known commonly as velvetmallows .
Viator picis is an extinct genus and species of lapwing ( Charadriiformes ; Charadriidae ; Vanellinae ) known only from the upper Pleistocene asphalt deposits known as the Talara Tar Seeps , which are found near Talara , northwestern Peru .
Adenium arabicum is a species of plant commonly used for bonsai and cultivated for its leaves , growth form and flowering characteristics .
Allium erdelii is a plant species found in Israel , Palestine Lebanon , Syria , Iraq , Egypt , Libya and Jordan .
Magnapinna atlantica , previously known as `` Magnapinna sp . A '' , is a species of bigfin squid known from only two specimens collected in the northern Atlantic Ocean .
Hydrophyllum brownei ( Brown 's waterleaf ) is a rare North American plant species found only in the Ouachita Mountains in Arkansas .
Myoxocephalus scorpioides , the arctic sculpin or the northern sculpin , is a predatory species of sculpin in the fish family Cottidae .
Brancsikia freyi is a species of praying mantis of the subfamily Deroplatyinae of the family Mantidae .
Platanthera sparsiflora is a species of orchid known by the common name sparse - flowered bog orchid .
Allanblackia floribunda , known in English as ' tallow tree ' , is a species of flowering plant in the Clusiaceae family that has been long used in traditional African medicine to treat hypertension .
The water springtail ( Podura aquatica ) is a species of springtail , one of only four described species in the family Poduridae .
Dorstenia choconiana is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Central America from Guatemala to Panama .
Maerua andradae is a species of plant in the Capparaceae family .
Chrysopilus asiliformis , the ' little snipefly ' , is a species of ' snipe flies ' belonging to the family Rhagionidae .
Bambusa ventricosa is a species of bamboo which is native to Vietnam and to Guangdong province in southern China .
Lycopodium magellanicum is a species of club moss that falls into the Lycopodium genus .
Scaphiopus is a genus of North American amphibian commonly referred to as the North American spadefoots , southern spadefoots , or eastern spadefoot toads .
Kokia kauaiensis , the Kauai treecotton or Kauaʻi Kokiʻo , is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family , Malvaceae , that is endemic to Kauaʻi , Hawaii .
Bursera bipinnata is a Mesoamerican species of trees widespread across Mexico and Central America from Chihuahua to Honduras .
Heterorhabditis heliothidis is a nematode species in the genus Heterorhabditis .
Vinca minor ( common names lesser periwinkle or dwarf periwinkle ) is a species of flowering plant native to central and southern Europe , from Portugal and France north to the Netherlands and the Baltic States , east to the Caucasus , and also southwestern Asia in Turkey .
Afronandus sheljuzhkoi , the Fourspine leaffish , is a species of Asian leaffish native to Ivory Coast .
Stathmostelma is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1893 .
Hadogenes troglodytes is a species of scorpion from southern Africa .
Buddleja montana is a species endemic to the rocky hillsides of the cordilleras of Peru at altitudes of 2,700 -- 4,000 m , extending into Bolivia ; it was named and described by Britton in 1898 .
Nephrurus amyae , commonly known as the rough knob - tailed gecko , is a species of gecko .
Salix taraikensis is a species of willow native to Hokkaidō ( Japan ) and Sakhalin ( Russia ) .
Talegalla is a genus of bird in the Megapodiidae family .
Teleocichla cinderella is a species of cichlid endemic to Brazil where it is found in the lower Tocantins River basin .
Myrmecia croslandi is a species of bull ant which is native to Australia .
Prionosciadium nelsonii is a plant species known from the Mexican states of Chiapas and Morelos .
Glutinoglossum exiguum is a species of earth tongue fungus that was described as new to science in 2015 .
Asperula orientalis ( known as Annual Woodruff or Oriental Woodruff ) is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Pristimantis educatoris is a species of frog found in Costa Rica , Panama , and Colombia .
Bolbitis heteroclita is an aquatic fern species of Bolbitis , native to the Indochina region of tropical Southeast Asia .
Raorchestes parvulus ( common names : Karin bubble - nest frog , tiny bubble - nest frog , dwarf bushfrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Barbus amanpoae is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Amanpoa River and the Uele River .
Geranium multiflorum is a rare species of geranium known by the common names manyflower geranium , or manyflowered cranesbill .
The Archbold 's owlet - nightjar ( Aegotheles archboldi ) is a species of bird in the Aegothelidae family .
Minolia ceraunia is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Oxythemis phoenicosceles , the Pepperpants , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Trichoparmenonta hoegei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichoparmenonta .
Erieopterus is a genus of prehistoric eurypterid found in Silurian to Devonian - aged marine strata of Europe and North America .
Although up to eight species have formerly been recognised in the genus Eoleptestheria , they are more usually all considered part of one species with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Bryopteris gaudichaudii is a species of liverwort in the Lejeuneaceae family .
Nesopupa plicifera is a species of very small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae .
Nematocharax venustus is a species of characin endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Jequitinhonha River basin .
Leptopodomorpha is an infraorder of insects in the order Hemiptera ( true bugs ) .
Pupfish are a group of small killifish belonging to ten genera of the family Cyprinodontidae of ray - finned fish .
Osmoxylon is a genus of flowering plant of family Araliaceae , comprising 60 species .
Atelecyclus undecimdentatus is a species of crab in the family Atelecyclidae .
Spermacoce brachysepala , the West Indian false buttonweed , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
Mauritiella is a dioecious genus of flowering plant in the palm family found in South America where it is commonly called buriti .
Plantago erecta is a host species for the Edith 's Checkerspot butterfly .
Luronium natans is a species of aquatic plant commonly known as the floating water - plantain .
Thalassodromidae ( meaning `` sea runners '' ) is a family of pterodactyloid pterosaurs from the early Cretaceous period of Brazil .
Leptosiphon nuttallii is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Nuttall 's linanthus .
Allium victorialis , commonly known as victory onion , Alpine leek , is a broad - leaved Eurasian species of wild onion .
Cottinella boulengeri , the short - headed sculpin , is a species of freshwater fish , a deepwater sculpin endemic to Lake Baikal in Russia .
Cytisus striatus is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names hairy - fruited broom , Portuguese broom , French broom and Spanish broom .
Christophia climacopterae is a species of snout moth in the genus Christophia .
Apluda is a genus of plants in the grass family native to Asia and to various islands in the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Gongxianosaurus is a genus of basal sauropod dinosaur from the early Jurassic Period ( Toarcian stage ) .
Cryptoclididae is a family of medium - sized plesiosaurs that existed from the middle Jurassic to the early Cretaceous period .
Cryptogramma crispa , the parsley fern , is an Arctic -- alpine species of fern .
The genus contains a single described species , Archiponera wheeleri known from several Late Eocene fossils which were found in North America .
Dactyloscopus pectoralis , the Whitesaddle stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Pacific coast of Baja California , Mexico and the Gulf of Mexico .
Brachyglottis huntii , commonly called rautini or Chatham Island Christmas tree , is a species in the Asteraceae family and is found only on the Chatham Islands in New Zealand .
Clarkia speciosa is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name redspot clarkia .
Lipophrys trigloides is a species of combtooth blenny .
Conus byssinus , common name the lesser butterfly cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Platanthera tescamnis , the intermountain bog orchid , is a species of orchid described in 2006 .
Phyllostachys aurea is a bamboo species of the ' running bamboo ' type , belonging to the diverse Bambuseae tribe .
Tagiades japetus , commonly known as the Pied Flat or the Common Snow Flat , is a species of spread - winged skipper butterfly belonging to the family Hesperiidae .
Cynodesmus is an extinct genus of omnivorous canine which inhabited North America during the Oligocene living from 33.3 - --26.3 Ma and existed for approximately 7 million years .
Acritopappus is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae described as a genus in 1972 .
Lycopus uniflorus is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name northern bugleweed .
Phyllostegia racemosa is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common names kiponapona and racemed phyllostegia .
Eulepetopsis vitrea is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Neolepetopsidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Clanculus philippii , common name Philippi 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Potamogeton clystocarpus is a rare species of flowering plant in the pondweed family known by the common name Little Aguja pondweed .
Allium hirtovaginatum is a species of wild onion native to the Mediterranean region , from Morocco and the Balearic Islands to Turkey .
Apotomops spomotopa is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family that is endemic to Peru .
Guibourtia coleosperma , aka African rosewood ( ambiguous ) , large false mopane , Rhodesian copalwood , and machibi , is a species of Guibourtia in the family Fabaceae .
Turbo fluctuosus , common name the wavy turban , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
The Mindoro racket - tail ( Prioniturus mindorensis ) is a species of parrot in the Psittaculinae family .
Kobyashiceras is an extinct genus in the cephalopod order Actinocerida , from Lower Devonian marine sediments in Japan .
It consists of a single species , namely Streptolirion volubile .
Artedius is a genus of sculpins native to the Pacific Ocean .
Desmoxytes rhinoceros is an aposematic species of dragon millipede in the genus Desmoxytes .
Aconitum lamarckii is a herbaceous plant species of the genus Aconitum in the family Ranunculaceae .
Pelargonium × fragrans , like its parent Pelargonium odoratissimum , is a small , spreading species which only grows up to 30 cm high and 60 cm wide .
Gilbertolus is a genus of dogtooth characins from northwestern South America , where restricted to the Atrato , Magdalena and Maracaibo basins .
Anthicus is a genus of ant - like flower beetles .
Gonimbrasia belina is a species of moth found in much of Southern Africa , whose large edible caterpillar , the mopani or mopane worm , is an important source of protein for millions of indigenous Southern Africans .
Discodorididae is a taxonomic family of sea slugs , specifically dorid nudibranchs , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Doridoidea .
Calguia defiguralis is a species of snout moth in the genus Calguia .
Heylerosauridae is a family of mastodonsauroid temnospondyls .
Ctenacodon is a genus of extinct mammal that lived in what is now North America during the Upper Jurassic period .
Anisomeles indica , with common name catmint , is a species of herbaceous plant native to eastern Asia and naturalized on some Pacific islands .
Aldisa andersoni is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cadlinidae .
Saurida filamentosa , the Threadfin saury , is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Western Pacific .
Tubastraea , also known as sun coral or sun polyps , is a genus of coral in the phylum Cnidaria .
Exerodonta smaragdina ( commonly known as the emerald tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Ligustrum pricei is a species of Ligustrum , native to China ( Guizhou , Hubei , Hunan , Shaanxi , Sichuan ) and Taiwan , where it occurs at 900 - -1700 m altitude .
Satyrium buchananii is a species of ground orchid occurring from Tanzania to Southern tropical Africa .
Falsodihammus strandiellus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Falsodihammus .
Euphorbia griffithii , the Griffith 's spurge , is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family Euphorbiaceae , native to Bhutan , Tibet and south west China .
Omphalepia dujardini is a species of snout moth in the genus Omphalepia .
Synalpheus carpenteri is a species of sponge - dwelling snapping shrimp described in 2006 from specimens collected from the Belizean Barrier Reef of the Exuma Islands , Bahamas , and the Atlantic coast of Panama .
Aulonocara jacobfreibergi , the eureka red peacock , is a species of fish in the Cichlidae family .
Parauna zikani is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parauna .
Trinchesia alpha is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Tergipedidae .
Anchomenus virescens is a species of ground beetle in the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Ukraine and southern part of Russia .
Sporobolus flexuosus is a species of grass known by the common name mesa dropseed .
Silene caucasica is a species of flowering plant in the family Caryophyllaceae .
Gemina is a genus of green alga .
Scrophularia lanceolata is a species of flowering plant in the figwort family known by the common name lanceleaf figwort .
Colchicum davisii is a large - flowering species native to Turkey .
Gentianaceae is a family of flowering plants of 87 genera and about 1600 species .
Microvelia is a genus of aquatic bug in the family Veliidae .
It contains the single species Mosquitoxylum jamaicense , which grows naturally from southern Mexico to Ecuador and also in Jamaica .
Species The only known species is Lamarckia aurea , the golden dog's - tail or goldentop grass It is an annual plant , typically 30 - 45 centimetres in height , with clusters of golden flowers in a panicle 5 - -8 cm long and 2 - 2.5 cm broad .
†Partula vittata was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Eleutherodactylus schmidti is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Hispaniola , and found in both the Dominican Republic and Haiti .
Luria controversa , the ' Controversial Isabella ' , is a species of cowry , a sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Baenoidea is a superfamily of extinct terrestrial and marine cryptordian turtles .
Beetles of the genus Helichus are found worldwide apart from in Australia and Antarctica .
It contains the single species Grucia monacheicauda , which is found in Mexico .
Alcides is a genus of uraniid moths from northern Australia , New Guinea , and other islands in the region .
Agyneta simplicitarsis is a species of sheet weaver found in Europe , Kazakhstan and Russia .
Leptodynerus is a palearctic genus of potter wasps .
Lanceola is a genus of green algae , in the family Characiaceae .
Suaeda vera , the alkali seepweed or shrubby sea - blite , is a species of plant in the Amaranthaceae family .
Acriopsis emarginata is a species of orchid endemic to Queensland .
Penstemon franklinii ( Franklin 's penstemon ) is a plant species endemic to Utah , known only from Cedar Valley in Iron County .
Cayratia geniculata is a species of plant native to Asia .
Paragoniates alburnus is a species of characin found in the Amazon River basin in Brazil , Peru , and Venezuela .
Abelisaurus ( /əˌbɛlᵻˈsɔːrəs/ ; `` Abel 's lizard '' ) is a genus of predatory abelisaurid theropod dinosaur during the Late Cretaceous Period ( Campanian ) of what is now South America .
Gnaphosa badia is a ground spider species found from Europe to Azerbaijan .
Pristobrycon striolatus is a species of serrasalmid .
Solanum furcatum is a species of nightshade known by the common name forked nightshade .
Conus janus , common name the janus cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Nitocrella is a genus of copepod .
Cyclocarya is a genus of flowering plants in the family Juglandaceae , comprising a single species Cyclocarya paliurus ( qing qian liu or wheel wingnut ) , formerly treated in the genus Pterocarya as Pterocarya paliurus .
Avimimus ( /ˌeɪvɨˈmaɪməs/ AY - vi - MY - məs ) , meaning `` bird mimic '' ( Latin avis = bird + mimus = mimic ) , was a genus of bird - like maniraptoran dinosaur that lived in the late Cretaceous in what is now Mongolia , around 70 million years ago .
Pseudelephantopus is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1792 .
Cardiocrinum giganteum , the giant Himalayan lily , is the largest species of any of the lily plants , growing up to 3.5 metres high .
Hymenaea martiana is a tree species in the genus Hymenaea found in Brazil ( Alagoas , Bahia , Ceara , Goias , Mato Grosso , Minas Gerais , Pernambuco ) and Paraguay .
Jiangxichelys is an extinct genus of nanhsiungchelyid turtle which existed in Ganzhou , Jiangxi Province , China during the latest Cretaceous epoch .
Eustenancistrocerus is an afrotropical , palearctic and oriental genus of potter wasps .
Silene schafta , the Caucasian campion or autumn catchfly , is a species of flowering plant in the family Caryophyllaceae , native to western Asia .
The Ichneumonidae are a parasitoid wasp family within the order Hymenoptera .
Solitas gruveli , the Guinea Flathead , is a species of flathead native to the eastern Atlantic Ocean along the African coast .
Whalleyana ( Viette , 1977 ) is an enigmatic genus of moths in the Lepidopteran group Obtectomera , endemic to Madagascar .
Psenopsis is a genus of medusafishes native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Aegista subchinensis ( 台灣大臍蝸牛 ; `` Taiwan 's umbilical snail '' ) is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Bradybaenidae .
Pachycereus schottii , the senita cactus , is a species of cactus from southern Arizona and north - western Mexico , particularly Baja California and Sonora .
Crataegus chrysocarpa is a species of hawthorn that is native to much of the continental United States and Canada .
Angustopila dominikae is a species of land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hypselostomatidae .
The genus Pulsatilla contains about 33 species of herbaceous perennials native to meadows and prairies of North America , Europe , and Asia .
The Arctic lemming ( Dicrostonyx torquatus ) is a species of rodents in the family Cricetidae .
Rubus phoenicolasius ( Japanese Wineberry , wine raspberry , or wineberry ) is an Asian species of raspberry ( Rubus subgenus Idaeobatus ) in the rose family .
Phyllobius arborator is a species of broad - nosed weevils belonging to the family Curculionidae , subfamily Entiminae .
Cantharidella balteata , common name the tessellated top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Nebria ambigua is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Tajikistan .
Mimagoniates lateralis is a species of tetra in the genus Mimagoniates .
The Emmelia trabealis , sometimes known as the Spotted Sulphur , is a species of moth of the family Noctuidae .
Pseudostrangalia cruentata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Pseudostrangalia .
Oeceoclades ambongensis is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is endemic to Madagascar .
Vampyroteuthidae is a family of vampyromorph cephalopods comprising the extant vampire squid , Vampyroteuthis infernalis , and the extinct Vampyronassa rhodanica from the Middle Jurassic .
Hypolepis ambigua , ( commonly known as pigfern ) is a species of fern that grows in New Zealand .
Labidochromis freibergi is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known to occur around Likoma Island in areas with rocky substrates .
Dysphania militaris is a species of moth of the Geometridae family that is found from in the tropical regions of South and Southeast Asia .
Cyclochila australasiae , commonly known as the green grocer , is a species of cicada and one of Australia 's most familiar insects .
The Meyer 's friarbird ( Philemon meyeri ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Tosena fasciata is a cicada species from Southeast Asia that has been recorded from Sumatra , Java , Borneo and Ambon Island
†Partula protracta was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .

Parvulastra exigua , or the dwarf cushion star is a species of sea star .
The Mindo robber frog or hornless groundfrog , Strabomantis necerus , is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Procerodidae is a family of marine triclads .
Pereskiopsis spathulata is the species of Pereskiopsis that is most commonly used when performing cactus seedling grafts .
Agaricus inapertus is a species of secotioid fungus in the genus Agaricus .
Hypaurotis is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae .
Magnolia liliifera was classified as having several varieties however these have now been generally accepted as species by several botanists including Hans Peter Nooteboom and Richard B. Figlar according to data compiled by Rafaël Govaerts , a researcher for the WCSP at Kew Gardens .
Alisma canaliculatum is a species of plants in the Alismataceae .
Palpada suprarufa is a species of flower fly first found in Ecuador .
Ctenochromis pectoralis , the Pangani Haplo ( short for `` haplochromine '' ) , is a species of fish in the Cichlidae family .

Beckianum beckianum is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae .
Pyrene flava , common name : the yellow dove shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
The Garden Grass - veneer ( Chrysoteuchia culmella ) is a species of moth of the family Crambidae .

Neochmia is a genus of estrildid finches found in Australasia .
Solidago ptarmicoides , the prairie goldenrod , white flat - top goldenrod or upland white aster a North American species of goldenrod in the sunflower family .

Almutaster is a North American genus of plants in the aster fammily containing the single species Almutaster pauciflorus ( formerly Aster pauciflorus ) , which is known by the common name alkali marsh aster .
Tabanus spodopterus also known as the black horned giant horsefly is a species of biting horse - fly .

Oxydactyla is a genus of microhylid frogs endemic to New Guinea .

Pseudocalliurichthys brevianalis , the Small ruddertail dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the coastal waters of Indonesia where it can be found at depths of from 0 to 6 metres ( 0 to 20 ft ) .

Thyasira trisinuata , common name the `` Atlantic cleft clam '' , is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Thyasiridae .

Streptomyces incanus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil of a hay meadow from the Cockle Park Experimental Farm in Northumberland in the United Kingdom .
Schistosoma nasale is a species of digenetic trematode in the family Schistosomatidae .
Nebria pazi is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Bejar and Gredos mountains of Spain .
It contains only one species , Antigambra amphitrocta , which is found in Zimbabwe and South Africa .

Conus barthelemyi , common name the Barthelemy 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .

The Persian jird ( Meriones persicus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Afghanistan , Armenia , Azerbaijan , Iran , Iraq , Pakistan , Turkey , and Turkmenistan .

Lonchoptera bifurcata is a species of spear - winged or pointed - winged fly in the family Lonchopteridae .

The Trans - Pecos striped whiptail ( Cnemidophorus inornatus heptagrammus ) is a subspecies of the little striped whiptail ( Cnemidophorus inornatus ) lizard .
Philovenator ( literally meaning `` love hunter '' ) is an extinct genus of troodontid paravian dinosaurs from the Wulansuhai Formation ( dated to the Campanian age , sometime between 75 and 71 million years ago ) of Inner Mongolia , China .

Labrisomus filamentosus , the Quillfin blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Caribbean Sea where they can be found on reefs with substantial algal growth .
