Heliocopris ( large dung beetles ) is a genus of Scarabaeidae or scarab beetles in the superfamily Scarabaeoidea .
Paroplocephalus atriceps , the Lake Cronin Snake is a species of snake in the Elapidae family .
Etoushanocertidae is an extinct family of ceratitid ammonite cephalopods that were restricted to marine strata in Late Permian China .
The Scolecomorphidae are the family of tropical caecilians ( Frost ) or African caecilians ( ITIS ) .
Hieracium bolanderi or Bolander 's hawkweed is a North American plant species in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Cynarctoides lemur is an extinct species of Cynarctoides , belonging to the subfamily Borophaginae and tribe Phlaocyonini , a canid endemic to various parts of central North America from the Late Oligocene to Miocene epoch ( Harrisonian stage ) living 24.8 - -20.6 mya and existed for approximately 4.2 million years .
Exochorda racemosa , pearlbush or common pearlbush , is a species of plant in the rose family .
Nepenthes rowaniae ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz ˈroʊ.əniː/ ; after Ellis Rowan , Australian naturalist and illustrator ) is a species of pitcher plant endemic to the Cape York Peninsula , Australia .
Austropotamobius pallipes is an endangered European freshwater crayfish , and the only species of crayfish native to the British Isles .
Pogostemon formosanus is a plant species in Lamiaceae , first described in 1896 .
Atelopus famelicus is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae endemic to Colombia .
Ivara is a small genus of sea snails , pyramidellid gastropod mollusks or micromollusks .
Micrurus nigrocinctus babaspul , or the Babaspul , is a subspecies of Micrurus nigrocinctus , more commonly known as the Central American Coral Snake .
Cucurbita radicans , commonly known in Mexico as Calabacilla ( little pumpkin / gourd ) or Calabaza de Coyote ( coyote gourd ) , is a species of gourd found growing wild , but also cultivated , in southern Mexico ( specifically in the Federal Districts of Jalisco , Mexico and Michoacán ) .
Collybia cookei is a species of fungus in the Tricholomataceae family , and one of three species in the genus Collybia .
Dentocorticium irregulare is a species of crust fungus in the family Polyporaceae .
Schoenicola is a genus of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
Juncus orthophyllus is a species of rush known by the common name straightleaf rush .
Eriogonum nidularium is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name birdnest buckwheat .
Gomphotherium ( /ˌɡɒmfəˈθɪəriəm/ ; `` Welded Beast '' ) is an extinct genus of proboscid that evolved in the Early Miocene of North America and lived for about 10 million years from 13.650 - -3.6 Ma .
Heterobranchus is a genus of airbreathing catfishes native to Africa .
Erigeron compositus is an Arctic and alpine species of fleabane in the daisy family .
Mann 's worm snake ( Typhlops manni ) is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Auricularia auricula - judae , known as the Jew 's ear , wood ear , jelly ear or by a number of other common names , is a species of edible Auriculariales fungus found worldwide .
Diversibipalium multilineatum is a species of large predatory land flatworm .
Allopeas gracile , common name the graceful awlsnail , is a species of small , tropical , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae .
Ammocrypta is a genus of perches , commonly known as the sand darters , native to Canada and the continental United States .
Amphiesma is a genus of colubrid snakes , commonly known as keelbacks because of their keeled dorsal scales .
Ctenosaura praeocularis , commonly known as the Southern Honduran Spiny - tailed Iguana , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Astranthium ciliatum , or Comanche western - daisy , is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Simarouba glauca is a species of flowering tree that is native to Florida in the United States , southern Florida , South America , and the Lesser Antilles .
Houstonia rubra , the red bluet , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
The Sri Lankan leopard ( Panthera pardus kotiya ) is a leopard subspecies native to Sri Lanka .
Dosinia concentrica , common name the `` West Indian dosinia '' , is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .
The Buller 's shearwater ( Ardenna bulleri ) is a Pacific species of seabird in the family Procellariidae ; it is also known as the grey - backed shearwater or New Zealand shearwater .
Allium insubricum is a plant species endemic to the Lombardy region in northern Italy .
Aldrovandia is a genus of fish in the family Halosauridae .
Blochius is a genus of prehistoric fish from the Eocene .
Pseudodyscrasis steyskali is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Pseudodyscrasis of the family Tephritidae .
Leptotyphlops telloi , or Tello 's thread snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Panicum repens is a species of grass known by many common names , including torpedograss , creeping panic , panic rampant , couch panicum , wainaku grass , quack grass , dog - tooth grass , and bullet grass .
The Taphrinomycetes are a class of ascomycete fungi belonging to the subdivision Taphrinomycotina .
Ageratina sodiroi is a species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Caledoniscincus is a genus of skinks ( a type of lizard ) .
Baylisascaris is a genus of roundworms that infect more than fifty animal species .
Miscanthus , silvergrass , is a genus of African , Eurasian , and Pacific Island plants in the grass family .
Rhabdolichops is a genus of glass knifefishes found in tropical South America .
Ophidion josephi is a fish species in the family Ophidiidae .
Amorphoscelis reticulata is a species of praying mantis that derives from Sarawak .
Docodonta is an order of extinct mammaliaforms that lived during the mid- to late - Mesozoic era .
Penicillium kongii is a terverticillate species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from plant leaves in China .
Caconemobius varius is a species of cricket known by the common name Kaumana cave cricket .
Farlowella henriquei is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Araguaia River basin .
Diodora rueppellii , common name the Rüppell 's keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Dizoniopsis coppolae is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from European waters , including the Greek Exclusive Economic Zone , Portuguese Exclusive Economic Zone , South West Coast of Apulia , and the Spanish Exclusive Economic Zone .
Ariocarpus bravoanus is a species of cactus which is endemic to San Luis Potosí in Mexico .
Nepenthes danseri ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz ˈdænsəraɪ/ ; after B. H. Danser , botanist ) is a species of tropical pitcher plant .
Abies fabri ( Faber 's fir ) is a conifer species in the family Pinaceae .
Buttonquail or hemipodes are members of a small family of birds , Turnicidae , which resemble , but are unrelated to , the quails of Phasianidae .
Petrotilapia chrysos is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from around the southern islands of Chinyankwazi and Chinyamwezi .
Pseudalidus fulvofasciculatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudalidus .
The Yemen linnet ( Linaria yemenensis ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Behemotops ( from the Biblical monster Behemoth , by Linnaeus and others believed to be a hippo ) is an extinct genus of herbivorous marine mammal .
Ichthyborus is a genus of distichodontid fishes found in tropical Africa , with these currently described species :
The Wrangel Island lemming ( Lemmus portenkoi ) is a species of lemming endemic to Wrangel Island in Russia .
Cheirolepidiaceae is a family of extinct coniferous plants .
Lauriidae is a family of land snails .
Taiwanajinga albofasciata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Taiwanajinga .
Odostemon quinquefolius is a shrub in the Berberidaceae family described as a species in 1918 .
The Firmicutes ( Latin : firmus , strong , and cutis , skin , referring to the cell wall ) are a phylum of bacteria , most of which have Gram - positive cell wall structure .
Cotinis fuscopicea is a species of Cotinis .
Ceramida moelleri is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily that can be found in Portugal and Spain .
Turrilitina is a proposed suborder of Cretaceous heteromorph ammonoid cephalopods derived from the Lytoceratidae in the Hauterivian stage of the Lower Cretaceous that would include the superfamilies Turrilitoidea , Ptychoceratoidea , and Scaphatoidea .
Leptosiphon acicularis ( syn . Linanthus acicularis ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name bristly linanthus .
Gasteroclupea is a genus of prehistoric clupeiform fish that is related to modern anchovies and herrings .
Micranthes oregana is a species of flowering plant known by the common name Oregon saxifrage .
Psilocybe subcubensis is an entheogenic species of mushroom in the Hymenogastraceae family .
Sairocaris is an extinct genus of crustacean , in the order Hoplostraca , that lived in the Mississippian age .
Sebecidae is an extinct family of prehistoric mesoeucrocodylian crocodylomorphs .
Carex haydeniana is a species of sedge known by the common name cloud sedge .
Cheiridopsis caroli - schmidtii is a species in the genus Cheiridopsis that consists of 100 flowering succulent perennial plants .
Draba breweri is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names cushion draba , Brewer 's draba , and Brewer 's Whitlow grass .
Based on 16S rDNA sequence analysis and the low degree of DNA relatedness between other members of Achromobacter species , Yabuuchi et al proposes that Alcaligenes denitrificans should be classified as a subspecies of Achromobacter xylosoxidans ( Alcaligenes xylosoxidans subsp . denitrificans ) .
Chameleons or chamaeleons ( family Chamaeleonidae ) are a distinctive and highly specialized clade of old world lizards with 202 species described as of June 2015 .
Cordia subcordata is a species of flowering tree in the borage family , Boraginaceae , that occurs in eastern Africa , South Asia , Southeast Asia , northern Australia and the Pacific Islands .
Orthotylus interpositus is a species of bug from the Miridae family that can be found in European countries such as Albania , Austria , Bulgaria , Czech Republic , France , Germany , Italy , Luxembourg , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , Slovenia , Spain , Switzerland , Ukraine , and southern part of Russia .
Perizoma affinitata , the rivulet , is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Chorizanthe uniaristata is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name one - awn spineflower .
Topografov virus is an enveloped , negative - sense RNA virus species of the genus hantavirus in the Bunyaviridae family .
Tornelasmias capricorni was a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
The type species is Gegepterus changi .
Abacopteris penangiana is a fern species in the genus Abacopteris .
Stenaulorhynchus is an extinct genus of hyperodapedontid rhynchosaur from Middle Triassic ( late Anisian stage ) deposits of Tanganyika Territory , Tanzania .
Hordeum marinum , commonly known as sea barley or seaside barley , is a species of grass .
Cerapachys fossulatus is a species of reddish brown army ant found in Sri Lanka and China .
Protilemoides buergersi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Protilemoides .
Colus pubescens , common name the hairy colus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Vahlkampfia is a genus of amoeboids in Heterolobosea .
Ptycholomoides aeriferana , the larch twist , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Ettlia terrestris is a species of green algae , in the family Chlorococcaceae .
The Bornean orangutan ( Pongo pygmaeus ) is a species of orangutan native to the island of Borneo .
Saccharomyces is a genus of fungi that includes many species of yeasts .
Middendorffinaia shadini is a species of unionid mussel endemic to South Primorye , Russia .
The Unalaska collared lemming ( Dicrostonyx unalascensis ) is a species of rodents in the family Cricetidae .
The Corimelaenidae are a family of shield bugs .
Stenotrema hirsutum , common name hairy slitmouth , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Polygyridae .
Eulophia alta is a species of orchid , known as the wild coco .
Omphalobasella inconspicua is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Omphalobasella .
Shuleichthys brachypteryx is an extinct species of bony fish which existed in China during the Cretaceous period .
Calumma crypticum , commonly known as the cryptic chameleon , is a species of chameleon found in Madagascar .
Tachina amurensis is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that can be found in Japan and Russia .
Dryopithecus was a genus of apes that is known from East Africa into Eurasia during the late Miocene period .
Oncidium ornithorhynchum is a species of orchid found from Mexico to Colombia .
Syzygium aqueum is a species of brush cherry tree .
Colpichthys is a genus of Neotropical silverside endemic to the Gulf of Mexico .
Hirudo orientalis is a species of medicinal leech .
Schistura udomritthiruji is species of stone loach , a riverine fish found in streams in southern Thailand .
The Palaeognathae are usually considered a superorder , but authors have treated them as a taxon as high as subclass ( Stresemann 1927 - -1934 ) or as low as an order ( Cracraft 1981 ) .
Panellus pusillus is a species of fungus in the family Mycenaceae .
Machaeranthera juncea ( syn . Xanthisma junceum ) is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names rush bristleweed or rush - like bristleweed .
Saussurea laniceps is pollinated by two generalist bumblebee species , Bombus rufofasticatus and Bombus festivus , that appear to specialize on Saussurea laniceps when it is flowering .
Scutalus mariopenai is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Bulimulidae .
Sympergoides nasutus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Sympergoides .
Maxillaria tenuifolia , the Delicate - leafed Maxillaria or Coconut Pie Orchid , is a species of orchid ranging from Mexico to Nicaragua and possibly Costa Rica .
Heliomeris soliceps is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family called the Tropical false goldeneye or paria sunflower .
Rita macracanthus is a species of bagrid catfish found in the Indus River drainage .
Inchoatia megdova is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails .
Sarcoscypha coccinea , commonly known as the scarlet elf cup , scarlet elf cap , or the scarlet cup , is a species of fungus in the family Sarcoscyphaceae of the order Pezizales .
Nassarius miga is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the nssa mud snails or dog whelks .
Cyanea koolauensis ( formerly Rollandia angustifolia ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common names Palolo Valley rollandia and narrowleaf rollandia .
Indirana gundia is a species of frog found in the Western Ghats of India .
Macrozamia riedlei , commonly known as zamia or zamia palm , is a species of plant in the Zamiaceae family .
Diplodactylus is a genus of geckos of the family Diplodactylidae from Australia .
Hieronymiella is a genus of South American plants in the Amaryllis family , known from only Bolivia and Argentina .
Paratrachichthys is a genus of slimeheads found in the Pacific Ocean .
Iciligorgia schrammi , common names deepwater sea fan and black sea fan is a species of gorgonian sea fan in the family Anthothelidae .
The Ginkgoaceae is a family of gymnosperms which appeared during the Mesozoic Era , of which the only extant representative is Ginkgo biloba , which is for this reason sometimes regarded as a living fossil .
Brassia pumila is a species of epiphytic orchid native to Guyana , Venezuela , French Guiana , Colombia , Peru , and Brazil .
Crataegus flava , summer haw , yellow - fruited thorn is a very rare species of hawthorn that was long known in cultivation in England but apparently is no longer grown .
Pelophila rudis is a species of black coloured ground beetle in Nebriinae subfamily which was described by John Lawrence LeConte in 1863 .
Yikezhaogia is an extinct genus of therocephalian therapsid from the Early Triassic of Mongolia .
Ossubtus xinguense is a species of serrasalmid and the only species of the genus Ossubtus .
Carabus perrini planus is a subspecies of black - coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Georgia , Russia , and Ukraine .
Pausinystalia brachythyrsum was a species of plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Delphinium trolliifolium is a species of larkspur known by the common names poison delphinium , cow poison , and Columbian larkspur .
More typically , Cardiodon has been assigned to Cetiosaurus , sometimes as a separate species Cetiosaurus rugulosus , in spite of its priority .
Gagea is a large genus of spring flowers in the lily family .
Vitrinula hahajimana is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrialgastropod mollusk in the family Ariophantidae .
Mabuya sloanii is a species of skink native to the Caribbean , where it is found in the Greater Antilles and in the northernmost Lesser Antilles .
Aldania is a butterfly genus of the Limenitidinae . The genus is confined to the temperate East Palearctic .
Antidesma bunius is a species of fruit tree in the Phyllanthaceae .
Progalesaurus is an extinct genus of non - mammalian therapsid .
Necrolestes patagonensis ( `` Grave Robber '' or `` Thief of the Dead '' ) is an extinct species of non - therian mammal , which lived during the early Miocene in what is now Argentine Patagonia .
Dymascus porosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Dymascus .
Haliotis dringi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Microsorum is a genus of over fifty species of tropical ferns .
The bee subfamily Andreninae is a nearly cosmopolitan lineage , with most of its diversity in one genus , Andrena , which contains over 1500 species .
Saxifraga hyperborea , the Pygmy saxifrage , is a plant species native to Canada , Alaska , Greenland , Russia , Spitsbergen , and from mountainous areas in the western United States .
Potamogeton wrightii , is an aquatic plant species in the genus Potamogeton .
Formosimyrma is a genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Formosimyrma lanuyensis .
Selysia bidentata is a species of the genus Selysia native to Panama .
Handleyomys rostratus , also known as the long - nosed oryzomys , long - nosed rice rat , or rusty rice rat is a species of rodent in the genus Handleyomys of family Cricetidae .
Duttaphrynus noellerti ( common name : Noellert 's toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Hemipepsis ustulata is a species of tarantula hawk native to the Southwestern United States .
Picrasma excelsa is a species of Picrasma in the family Simaroubaceae .
Perideridia erythrorhiza is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names western yampah and redroot yampah .
Whipplea is a monotypic genus containing the single species Whipplea modesta , which is known by several common names including common whipplea , yerba de selva , and modesty .
Verrucosispora gifhornensis is a member of the actinobacterial familyMicromonosporaceae , being the type species of its genus .
Parmacella tenerifensis is a species of air - breathing land slug , a shell - less terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Parmacellidae .
Allium ebusitanum is a plant species known from the Spanish Island of Ibiza in the Balearic Islands , as well as from Tunisia and Algeria .
Heterorhachis is a genus of South African flowering plants in the daisy family .
Cyathea glauca is a species of tree fern endemic to Réunion .
Belostoma flumineum is a North American species of giant water bug ( family Belostomatidae ) .
Pomadasys is a genus of grunts native to the waters of the eastern Atlantic Ocean and through the Indian Ocean to the Pacific coast of the Americas .
Pedobacter nyackensis is a species of Gram - negative , rod - shaped , non - spore - forming eubacterial species .
Clavulicium is a genus of corticioid fungi in the family Stereopsidaceae .
Echinochloa is a very widespread genus of plants in the grass family .
Shelania is an extinct genus of prehistoric frogs that lived in South America during the Eocene .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Peyerimhoffiella elegans .
Mackilligin 's gerbil , Dipodillus mackilligini ( sometimes misspelled mackillingini ) , also known as Mackilligin 's dipodil , is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Tulipa agenensis is a Middle Eastern species of flowering plants in the lily family .
Genianthus is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1883 .
Limacus is considered as a subgenus of the genus Limax .
Chorda filum , commonly known as dead man 's rope or sea lace among other names , is a species of brown algae in the genus Chorda .
Zostera capricorni is a species of eelgrass native to the seacoasts of New Guinea , Queensland , New South Wales , Victoria , South Australia , Norfolk Island and the North Island of New Zealand .
Its only species , Mimomantis milloti , is found in Madagascar .
Paragorgopsis fascipennis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Paragorgopsis of the family Ulidiidae .
Arthrobacter roseus is a species of red - pigmented psychrophilic bacteria first isolated from a cyanobacterial mat . Its type strain is CMS 90r(T ) (= MTCC 3712 T = DSM 14508 T ) .
Huvenia is a genus of extinct plants of the Early Devonian ( Pragian or Siegenian stage , around 411 to 408 million years ago ) , found in slate deposits of the Rhenish Massif .
Yarrella is a genus of lightfishes .
Suillus helenae is a species of bolete fungus in the genus Suillus .
The Alvinellidae are a family of small , deep - sea polychaete worms endemic to hydrothermal vents in the Pacific Ocean .
Supplanaxis nucleus , common name the black Atlantic planaxis , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Planaxidae .
Ophiogomphus cecilia , the green snaketail or green gomphid is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Clintonia andrewsiana is a species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common names Andrews clintonia and red clintonia .
Mitra variabilis , common name : the variable mitre , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters or miter snails .
Caracolus is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Pleurodontidae .
Penicillium chalybeum is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from dried fish in Sri Lanka .
Eleutheromenia is a genus of cavibelonian solenogasters , a kind of shell - less , worm - like mollusk .
Drakaea thynniphila , commonly known as narrow - lipped hammer orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Lycaena dorcas is a species of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae , the gossamer - winged butterflies .
Uarbryichthys ( `` Uarbry Fish '' ) is a genus of primitive teleost ray - finned fish from fossil beds near the Talbragar River Bed .
Fraser 's eagle - owl ( Bubo poensis ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Gynnidomorpha permixtana , the coast conch , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Corydoras paleatus is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Callichthyidae .
Rhododendron niveum ( Chinese : 西藏毛脉杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to northeastern India ( including Sikkim ) , Bhutan , and southern Tibet in China , where it grows at altitudes of 2600 - -3500 meters .
Bullia laevissima , common name the fat plough shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Thuringothyris is an extinct genus of Early Permian eureptiles known from the Thuringian Forest in central Germany .
Deepstaria is a genus of jellyfish known for their thin , sheet - like bodies .
Yolanda 's tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys yolandae ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Juglans jamaicensis ( West Indian walnut , nogal , palo de nuez ) is a species of walnut in the Juglandaceae family .
Sedum oaxacanum is a species of flowering plant in the stonecrop family .
Sinopieris is a genus of butterflies in the family Pieridae . The genus occurs in Nepal , Tibet , Yunnan , Gansu , Shaanxi and Sichuan . All six pecies were originally included in Pieris .
Brachysomida atra is the species of the Lepturinae subfamily in longhorn beetle family .
Penstemon rupicola is a species of penstemon known by the common name cliff beardtongue .
Retilla indigens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Retilla .
Agelastica alni , the alder leaf beetle , is a species of leaf beetle ( Chrysomelidae ) in the genus Agelastica .
Mimotriammatus nigrosignatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimotriammatus .
Libellula doris is an extinct species of dragonflies , commonly called skimmers , in the family Libellulidae .
Nitrobacteraceae is a family of Alphaproteobacteria .
Acanthobrama tricolor , or the Damascus bream , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Panicum amarum is a species of grass known by the common name bitter panicgrass .
Leptaspis is a genus of Paleotropical plants in the grass family , native to Africa , southern Asia , northern Australia , and a few islands of the western Pacific .
Oberea balineae is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Heller in 1915 .
Microsomatidia reticulata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Microsomatidia .
Heteroconger cobra , sometimes known as the cobra garden eel , is a species of garden eel of the family Congridae , found in the western Central Pacific from Honiara , the Solomon Islands to Port Moresby , Papua New Guinea .
Lottia scabra or the rough limpet is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Lottiidae .
Melica subulata is a species of grass known by the common name Alaska oniongrass .
Amanita nehuta , also called Maori Dust Amanita , is a species of fungus in the Amanitaceae family .
The Chinese broad - headed pond turtle ( Chinemys megalocephala ) is a species of turtle in the Geoemydidae family .
Tagetes pusilla , the lesser marigold , is a Latin American species of marigolds in the sunflower family .
Aplastodiscus leucopygius is a species of frog in the family Hylidae , endemic to Brazil .
Paralissotes reticulatus , also called the New Zealand Reticulate Stag Beetle is a native species of stag beetle from New Zealand .
Stephanomeria paniculata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names tufted wirelettuce and stiff - branched wirelettuce .
Anomiopus idei is a species of true dung beetle that is endemic to Perú , and is only known from its type locality in Loreto Region .
Begonia aequilateralis Irmsch . , 1929 is a species of begonia known only from the Sungai Buloh area of Selangor , Peninsular Malaysia .
Malacothamnus fasciculatus , with the common names chaparral mallow and Mendocino bushmallow , is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family .
Pleurocoronis pluriseta is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name bush arrowleaf .
Allobates bromelicola ( common name : coastal rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Iflaviridae is a family of positive sense RNA viruses insect - infecting viruses .
Gilia salticola is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name salt gilia .
Alburnus schischkovi is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus , that can be found in Bulgaria in river Veleka , and Turkey in river Rezovska .
The Mygalomorphae or mygalomorphs are an infraorder of spiders .
Ecsenius aroni , known commonly as the Aron 's blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Indian ocean .
Hibiscus moscheutos ( rose mallow , swamp rose - mallow , crimsoneyed rosemallow , eastern rosemallow ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Malvaceae .
Comarostaphylis diversifolia , known by the common names summer holly and California comarostaphylos , is a species of shrub in the heath family .
Lilium davidii is an Asian species of plants in the lily family , native to mountainous areas of Assam , Manipur , Arunachal Pradesh , Tibet , Bhutan , Hubei , Shaanxi , Sichuan , Guizhou , and Yunnan .
Bufoides is a genus of true toads ; the only known species is the Mawblang toad or Khasi Hills toad , M. meghalayanus .
Giraffa jumae is an extinct species of even - toed mammal in the Giraffidae family .
Ithomia avella is a Neotropical species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Senecio medley - woodii is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae .
Barbicambarus cornutus is a species of crayfish found only in the Barren River and Green River systems of Tennessee and Kentucky .
Parabybe subfoveolata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parabybe .
Alveolinidae is a family of spheroidal to fusiform milioline foraminfera with multiple apertures and complex interiors in which chambers are subdivided into chamberlets and subfloors interconnected by passageways .
Imbrasia epimethea is a species of moth belonging to the Saturniidae family .
Phyllanthus mirabilis is a plant species of family Phyllanthaceae endemic to Thailand .
Exapion is a genus of straight - snouted weevils .
Melanodexia is a peculiar New World cluster fly genus of the western United States .
Oxyloma patentissima is a species of land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
Cardamine lyrata , known commonly as Japanese cress and Chinese ivy , is a species of aquatic plant in the mustard family .
Tridentiger kuroiwae is a species of goby endemic to Japan where it is found in flowing fresh waters .
Arthragrostis is a genus of Australian plants in the grass family , found only in Queensland .
Kutara is a leafhopper genus belonging to the Selenocephalinae subfamily .
Scapteriscus vicinus , the tawny mole cricket , is a species of insect in the mole cricket family , Gryllotalpidae .
Pletholax gracilis is a species of lizard in the family Pygopodidae , the only species in the genus Pletholax .
Many species previously included in the genus Porphyra has transferred to Pyropia , for example Pyropia tenera and Pyropia yezoensis .
Purana nebulilinea is a cicada species distributed in peninsular Malaysia , Sumatra , Borneo and nearby smaller islands .
Sutilizonidae is a taxonomic family of sea snails , deepwater hydrothermal vent snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Antarctic dragonfishes are a family , Bathydraconidae , of deep - sea perciform fishes .
Dilsea carnosa , commonly known as the poor man 's weather glass or the sea belt , is a species of red algae in the Dumontiaceae family of the order Gigartinales .
Nathalie Manfrino is a French `` soprano '' .
Marilyn Tyler is an American operatic soprano , former director of Opera Studies and Emeritus Faculty Member at the University of New Mexico .
Vito Giuseppe Millico , called `` Il Moscovita '' ( 19 January 1737 -- 2 October 1802 ) was an Italian soprano castrato , composer , and music teacher of the 18th century who is best remembered for his performances in the operas of Christoph Willibald Gluck .
Joan Rodgers C.B.E. ( Whitehaven , 1956 ) is an English operatic soprano .
Marthe Chenal ( 1881 -- 28 January 1947 ) was a French operatic soprano who had an active singing career between 1905 and 1923 .
Mohammed El - Bakkar ( Arabic : محمد البكار‎ ; died in Pawtucket , Rhode Island , United States , September 8 , 1959 ) was a Lebanese tenor , oud player , and conductor .
Isabella Lampe ( also Isabella Young ) ( December 1715 , London -- 5 January 1795 , London ) was an English operatic soprano and the wife of composer John Frederick Lampe .
Wojtek Drabowicz ( also Wojciech Drabowicz ) ( 24 March 1966 -- 27 March 2007 ) was a Polish operatic baritone who was a leading performer at the Polish National Opera from 1989 through 2007 .
Lawrence Zazzo ( born December 15 , 1970 in Philadelphia ) is an American countertenor .
Giuseppina Huguet ( 1871 - -1951 ) was a Catalan operatic soprano with a lyrical voice who sang throughout Europe prior to World War I. Huguet was born in 1871 and registered on official documents as `` Josefina '' Huguet .
Kobie van Rensburg ( born on 23 May 1969 in Johannesburg ) is a South African tenor and opera director .
Pia Ravenna ( born Hjördis Sophie Tilgmann ; 25 October 1894 -- 19 October 1964 ) was a celebrated Finnish coloratura soprano who specialized in operatic works and was known as `` the Nightingale of Finland '' .
Yvonne Brothier ( born on 6 June 1889 in Saint - Julien - l'Ars , Vienne , died Paris , 22 January 1967 ) was a soprano operatic singer who worked principally at the Opéra - Comique , Paris .
Marie Sundelius ( 4 February 1882 - 27 June 1958 ) was a Swedish - American classical soprano .
Clara Pierre Impens ( 21 February 1899 -- 16 August 1970 ) was a Belgian soprano who sang under the stage - name Clara Clairbert .
Sally Bradshaw is a British high mezzo soprano who made a career principally as a Baroque specialist in opera and concerts .
Alice Zeppilli ( 28 August 1885 -- 14 September 1969 ) was a French operatic soprano of Italian heritage who had an active international singing career from 1901 to 1930 .
Riki Guy ( Hebrew : ריקי גאי‎ ) ( born c. 1975 ) is an Israeli full - lyric soprano .
Joseph Maas ( 30 January 1847 in Dartford , England -- 16 January 1886 in London ) was an English tenor singer .
Ludmila Vernerová ( born 1962 ) is a Czech operatic soprano and the niece of oboist Pavel Verner .
Sissel Kyrkjebø ( Norwegian pronunciation : ( ˈsɪsəl ˈçʏʁçəˌbʷøː ) , /ˈsisel ˈçyrçeˌbø/ ; born 24 June 1969 ) , also simply known as Sissel , is a Norwegian soprano .
James Reed Miller ( February 29 , 1880 -- December 29 , 1923 ) , who recorded as Reed Miller and as James Reed , was an American tenor who had an active career as a concert and oratorio singer during the first quarter of the 20th century .
Lois Hunt ( November 26 , 1924 -- July 26 , 2009 ) was an American lyric soprano who had spent some of her earlier career performing at New York City 's Metropolitan Opera and later spent four decades performing and recording classical music and musical theater numbers nationwide together with baritone Earl Wrightson .
Giangiacomo Guelfi ( 21 December 1924 -- 8 February 2012 ) was an operatic baritone , particularly associated with Verdi and Puccini .
Clare Shore ( born 1954 ) is an American composer , music educator mezzo - soprano , and conductor .
Valeriano Pellegrini ( c. 1663 -- 18 January 1746 ) was an Italian soprano castrato singer of the 18th century .
Eleanor Greenwood is a mezzo soprano and graduate of the Royal Academy of Music in London .
Zinka Milanov ( Croatian pronunciation : ( zîːŋka milǎnɔv̞ ) ) ( May 17 , 1906 -- May 30 , 1989 ) was a Croatian - born operatic spinto soprano who had a major career centred on the New York Metropolitan Opera .
Louise Grandjean ( 1870 - -1934 ) was a French operatic soprano who was particularly admired for her portrayals of Wagner and Verdi heroines .
Bernard Ładysz ( born 24 July 1922 , Wilno , then Poland ) is a Polish opera singer ( bass - baritone ) and actor .
Nino Martini ( 7 August 1902 , Verona , Italy -- 9 December 1976 , Verona , Italy ) was an Italian operatic tenor and actor .
Emilio De Marchi ( Italian pronunciation : ( eˈmiljo deˈmarki ) ; January 6 , 1861 -- March 20 , 1917 ) was an Italian operatic tenor .
John van Kesteren ( born May 4 , 1921 , The Hague - died July 11 , 2008 , Jupiter , Florida ) was a Dutch operatic tenor .
Pier Miranda Ferraro ( October 30 , 1924 -- January 18 , 2008 ) was an Italian operatic tenor who had an active international opera career from 1951 through 1981 .
Ruby Elzy ( February 20 , 1908 -- June 26 , 1943 ) , was a pioneer American operatic soprano .
Jamie Barton ( born 1980/1981 ( age 34 - -35 ) ) is an American operatic mezzo - soprano .
John Fiorito ( born 4 September 1936 in New York ) is a baritone opera singer .
Muriel Foster ( 22 November 1877 -- 23 December 1937 ) was an English contralto , excelling in oratorio .
Gary Griffiths ( born 22 April 1983 ) is a Welsh baritone from the village of Pembrey , near Llanelli , Wales .
Karl Ridderbusch ( 29 May 1932 -- 21 June 1997 ) was a German operatic bass , associated in particular with the music of Wagner .
